title: grandma's butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter, then add brown sugar and 1 tablespoon water. Cook until mixture makes a thick syrup.
Add milk, egg yolks and a mixture of white sugar and flour.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine all but oil; mix thoroughly.
Gradually add oil, beating all the time.
Bottle and store in refrigerator.
Use on cabbage or greens, just before serving.

title: sugar twin apple spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spray a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with Baker's Joy nonstick cooking spray. Mix flour, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread according to package directions.
Mix the last 3 ingredients.
Put 1/2 of the corn bread crumbs in a bowl; add chopped pepper as first layer.
Put two of the chopped tomatoes next, then add layer of onions.
Spread the other two tomatoes.
Add the bacon.
Next, put the mayonnaise on top of the bacon.
Spread remaining 1/2 of the corn bread crumbs on top and refrigerate.
It will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat. Stir in vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Gradually adding to cream mixture.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: gourmet pasta
directions: Layer 1/2 noodles and 1/2 meat.
Repeat in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.

title: golobki (cabbage) casserole
directions: Place chopped cabbage in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Brown meat and onions.
Pour off fat.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spread meat over cabbage with spoon.
Mix tomato soup with water and pour over mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is soft.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken, onions and vegetables in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend thoroughly. Add chicken stock slowly and salt.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken mixture.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Take a package of boneless stew beef that has been cut into chunks.
Add cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix and water.
Mix all together in baking dish; cover tightly and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheese and garlic potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes in liquid. Add salt and garlic. Boil for about 5 minutes, then add milk and cheese. Simmer until cheese melts. Sprinkle top with paprika or black pepper.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients (except rolls); mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: microwave jiffy pizzas
directions: Slice
pitas
into
6-inch rounds; toast under broiler. Place 4
rounds,	toasted
side
up, on waxed paper.
Combine tomato paste,
water,
oil, honey and spices in a small bowl; spread over top surface of pita rounds, dividing equally among all
8.	Divide salami
among
the
sprinkle
with sliced mushrooms;
top with
cheese.
Microwave
on High, uncovered, about
4 minutes each batch or until cheese is melted;
rotate 1/4 turn every 30 seconds.
Makes 8 mini pizzas.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix the rest into the first.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove immediately from pans.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook onion and pepper until golden.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
I add water as needed.

title: rolls
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, salt and hot water to melt margarine.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine mixtures. Beat eggs and add.
Stir in flour.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for several days.
When you want rolls, pinch off walnut-sized portions of dough, working into a ball with floured hands.
Place about an inch apart on greased pans.
Let rise in a warm, draft-free place, covered with a lightweight dish towel for a couple of hours.
Bake at 375° until golden (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cookie cups
directions: You will need Pam (to grease bottom of muffin pan).

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling. Set in refrigerator until firm. Cream sour cream, sugar and cream cheese. Spread on top of Jell-O and sprinkle with nuts.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix in egg, salt and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: hot cole slaw
directions: Bring to a boil, vinegar, water, salt, sugar, spices and oil. Remove from heat.
Add vinegar mixture to the beaten eggs and whipping cream.
Cook for another 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over cabbage and pickle mixture and serve.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put in large pot and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until seasonings are blended.
If too thick, add more tomato juice.

title: welsh plum pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and fill greased pudding molds or baking powder cans, leaving room for swelling.
Cans are covered, then boiled for 6 hours.
Serve with a sauce flavored with brandy or whiskey.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook sliced carrots until almost done.
Drain.
Melt margarine in pan and cook onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until cheese melts and thickens.
Add to carrots. Sprinkle 2 cups buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: freezer peach jam
directions: Peel, pit and finely chop peaches; measure 3 1/2 cups into a large bowl.
Add lemon peel and ascorbic acid.
Combine the 1/4 cup sugar and pectin.
Gradually add pectin mixture to the peach mixture, stirring vigorously.
Let mixture stand 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Slowly stir the 3 cups sugar into the peach mixture; stir until sugar dissolves.
Ladle jam at once into clean jars or freezer containers, leaving a 1/2-inch head space. Wipe the rims and seal.
Let the jam stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Chill and put in freezer.
Will keep frozen 3 months. Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Using frozen pie crust or your own, mix together all the sliced apples, 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Fill pie shell.

title: surprise shortcake
directions: Slice strawberries; reserve some for the top of the cake. Crush half of the berries and mix with 1/2 cup sugar.
Prepare the Dream Whip.
Trim crusts from the bread.
Butter one side of the bread; sprinkle with sugar.
Measure 1/2 cup syrup from the berries and set aside.
Line bottom of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with bread, buttered side up, trimming slices if necessary to fit pan.
Spoon half the strawberries on bread and 1 cup Dream Whip.
Repeat until last layer from top.
Last layer of bread should be buttered side down.
Drizzle with syrup.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 3 hours.
Invert onto serving platter.
Frost with Dream Whip and garnish with remaining strawberries.

title: stromboli
directions: Let dough rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down. Roll loaves together into one 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Layer ham and pepperoni on half of the dough (lengthwise).
Sprinkle with onion and green pepper.
Top with 1/4 cup of pizza sauce.
Layer Mozzarella, cappicola, salami and Provolone over sauce.
Sprinkle with basil, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Spread another 1/4 cup of pizza sauce on top.
Fold plain half of dough over filling and seal edges well.
Place on a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Brush with melted butter.
Heat the remaining pizza sauce and serve with sliced stromboli.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple and blueberries in medium saucepan.
Add enough water to make 2 cups juice.
Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin mix.
Mix with nuts, pineapple and blueberries.
Congeal in a shallow 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a 3 quart microproof casserole, combine onion, green pepper and butter.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on HI for 4-5 minutes, or until onion is transparent.
Add tomotoes, wine and flour; stir until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chicken.
Cover and cook on HI for 7 minutes.
Add chicken pieces, immersing in sauce.
Cover and cook on HI for 20-25 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Stir once during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 4-6.
Total cooking time:
31-37 minutes.

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Toss bits of bread in melted butter and cover top of casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
To make a 9 x 13-inch pan size casserole, double this recipe.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine rolled oats, flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add melted butter to oatmeal mixture and mix with fork or pastry blender until well blended.
Arrange fruit in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or 2-quart baking dish.
Spread oatmeal mixture on top of fruit.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender and crust is brown.
Serve warm or cold with milk, cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked alaska strawberry shortcake
directions: Foil line an 8-inch round pan; spoon in ice cream.
Freeze firm.
Combine biscuit mix and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat together milk, yolk and butter; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth. Spread in greased 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Place ice cream on shortcake; top with fruit.
Place on board.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder, mixing well. Combine shrimp, celery, onion and rice.
Stir in mayonnaise mixture; toss lightly.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: etta's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and onion.
Add sauerkraut, sausage, 1/4 cup bread crumbs and mix well.
Shape in 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Roll in flour and dip in milk, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil for 1-2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Can be frozen.

title: beef chop suey
directions: Brown steak in a little oil.
Add celery, onion and garlic to meat; simmer on low heat.
Then add chop suey vegetables and bean sprouts (do not drain).
Then add soy sauce and bouillon cubes. Simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over rice and chop suey noodles.

title: broccoli chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone it.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
In a large casserole dish, put rice, chicken, onion, bell pepper, broccoli, Cheez Whiz and soup. Mix well and season with salt and pepper.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the vanilla pudding.
Cover the bottom of bowl with Nilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour in pudding mix.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.
(Layer it.)

title: nacho dip
directions: In a crock-pot, melt Velveeta cheese.
When melted, add browned beef and jalapeno sauce.
Serve as a dip with nacho chips. Add a little milk to thin it if it is too thick.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons oleo.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Melt jello and sugar in water.
Add frozen strawberries and mix well.
If strawberries are large, slit them.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Combine cornflakes, mustard, pepper, paprika and garlic powder.
In a shallow bowl, combine egg white and lemon juice; beat slightly.
Dip chicken in egg mixture; coat with crumb mixture.
Place in ungreased baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until done.
Do not turn during baking.

title: husband's delight(mine, for sure!)
directions: In a bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions; set aside. Brown the meat in butter; add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Cook noodles according to package directions.

title: green bean salad
directions: In medium bowl, place beans, mushrooms and onion.
In small bowl, stir together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and chill until serving time.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip until well mixed.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: pink salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in large mixing bowl.
Add jello until completely dissolved.
When the pineapple is completely drained, add that to the cottage cheese mixture and mix completely by hand. Add walnuts and marshmallows.
Add Cool Whip.
Don't mix or whip it in.
Fold in easily until blended well.
Better if you refrigerate overnight.

title: weight watchers chicken ala grecque
directions: In medium bowl, not aluminum, combine chicken and lemon juice and turn to coat with juice.
Let marinate 10 minutes.
Combine flour and oregano on plate or in plastic bag.
Remove chicken from marinade, allowing juice to drip into bowl; reserve juice.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture, coating both sides.

title: chocolate sundae cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand until cool.

title: broccoli-stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion; cook until onion is tender but not browned.
Remove from heat; let cool.
In a
large bowl, stir Ricotta cheese and egg.
Add broccoli and Jack cheese.
Mix well. In a large kettle of boiling water, cook pasta 8 to 10 minutes until tender but firm to the bite; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain again.
Stuff each shell with 2 tablespoons broccoli-cheese mixture.

title: strawberry torte(nice to serve at christmas!  super!)
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk, cool.
Fold whipped cream into marshmallows and spread on cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in strawberries.
When thick, spread on cream layer.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon; add onion and saute.
Stir in remaining ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and baked later.

title: v b s 1984 - africa
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Top with peanuts.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine butter, eggs, sugar, baking soda, vanilla, cinnamon and flour in a large bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Add apples and nuts.
Stir to mix.
Scrape into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cut into 36 squares.
Enjoy!

title: southwestern chicken 'n shells
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine vinegar, salt and pepper; toss with beef.
Cover and marinate for 30 minutes; drain.
Place flour in a bowl; add beef and toss to coat.

title: rice krispie buckeyes
directions: Mix
well
Rice Krispies, peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine.	Form
into small balls. Stick toothpicks into balls and
dip
into
the
mixture
of
chocolate morsels and Parowax, which you make by melting in a double boiler.

title: meatballs
directions: Simmer till brown 1 hour.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light. Add fruit cocktail with juice and dry ingredients; mix well and add nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a greased jelly roll pan.

title: favorite cheese ball
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with drained pineapple.
Add onion and green pepper.
Form into ball.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Mix cherries and walnuts together.
Cover cheese ball with mixture. Enjoy with favorite crackers and pretzel sticks.

title: lemon yogurt sponge torte
directions: Spread the coconut on a large baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 4 minutes or until golden.
Lightly grease a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Line pan with waxed paper (grease the paper).

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk, Bran Buds in boiling water, flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add dry Bran Buds and raisins.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° in muffin tins.
(Texas size muffins, 20 minutes.)
Batter may be kept up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator in a covered container.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Combine hot cooked potatoes and black pepper.
Add melted butter and dill.
Toss lightly and serve hot.

title: catsup barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in fat until brown, then add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake in four layers at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes; cool.

title: brownie nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brownie mix, biscuit mix, water, eggs, oil & vanilla with mixer.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and raisins.
Pour batter into 2 slightly greased non-stick loaf pans.
Bake 45-50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks 10 minutes longer.
Serve warm with creamy cinnamon spread found in this book.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion, pepper and hamburger meat.
Combine meat, ketchup, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire.
Pour into pork and beans; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Line baking pan with foil. Salt and pepper chicken pieces. Dip in melted margarine.
Coat with crumbs. Place in pan, not crowded.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not turn.

title: on the run chicken fingers
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Whisk buttermilk, garlic, celery salt and Tabasco.
Pour mixture over chicken and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Mix breadcrumbs with paprika and cheese until well blended.
Lift chicken strips, one at a time, out of buttermilk mixture and coat with breadcrumb mixture.
Freeze breaded strips (do not allow them to touch) on a baking sheet until firm, then package in a plastic freezer bag, seal and return to freezer.
To bake, heat oven to 450° and arrange frozen strips about 1/2-inch apart on a foil lined baking sheet sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until crisp and golden.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a large bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: christmas card cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir flour with spices and soda; add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Cover and chill until firm (2 hours).
Remove from refrigerator.
On floured surface, roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes with cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove to rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble cheese; add sour cream and juice of one large lemon; salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: cheddar cheese canape
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Lightly toast the muffins and then spread with mixture.
Cut in 4 pieces and place on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt and add to the creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 round cake pans. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Put egg yolks into a large bowl.
Add sugar and beat until thick.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients (except egg whites) to egg yolk mixture, blending well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.
Various fruits such as peaches, strawberries, etc., can be added.

title: dutch honey
directions: Heat syrup and sugar on top of stove.
When starts to boil, remove from heat.
Add milk, stirring all the time, until it gets hot.
Use on pancakes or hot biscuits.

title: polish sausage
directions: Cut Polish sausage into bite size pieces.
Place all ingredients into a frying pan; cover and simmer 10 to 20 minutes.

title: momma's butter and egg bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Set aside.
Bring 1 cup water and butter to boil.
Turn off burner.
Set aside.
Let cool to warm.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup cold water, sugar, salt and egg.
To this, add water, butter and yeast (making sure the water is not too hot to kill the yeast).
Stir in enough flour to form dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead for 10 to 15 minutes.
Continue adding flour as needed.
Set in a warm place to rise until doubled.
Punch down and knead again.
Form into rolls or loaf.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown, rolls about 25 minutes, loaf about 1 hour.
Cool on cooling rack.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook butter, sugar and onion until golden.
Add broth and water; simmer 45 minutes.
Top with garlic toast and cheese.
Bake at 400° until toasted and cheese melts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly hash brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Melt butter and add cocoa.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cover with marshmallows and return to oven until
marshmallows are slightly melted.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate frosting over marshmallows.
Cool before cutting.
Yields 48 brownies.

title: blueberry bran muffins
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg and milk and add to flour mixture.
Add shortening and mix only enough to moisten flour.
Fold in cereal and blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 medium muffins.
Muffins may be baked and then frozen.
To serve, thaw muffins completely, then heat on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, oleo and vanilla; add eggs.
Beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in almond bark or chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: chart house bleu cheese dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients and blend 2 minutes at low speed.
Add mayonnaise and blend 1/2 minute at low speed, then increase speed to medium and blend an additional 2 minutes.
Slowly add Bleu cheese and blend at low speed no longer than 4 minutes.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
If too thick, thin with a little milk.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Cream the butter and cheese. Add flour and pepper to form dough.
Using 1 teaspoon of dough, wrap around olive.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
(Can be made ahead and reheated.)

title: party cocktail sausage
directions: Heat jelly and sauce until jelly has melted, then add the sausages and let simmer until sausages are heated through.
You can also use barbecue sauce instead of the mixture.
Can use in a crock-pot or fondue pot.

title: city bakery's burgers(veggie burgers)
directions: In a 10-12 inch nonstick frying pan over medium heat, cook onion and garlic in butter, stirring often, until onion is golden; about 8 minutes.
Add cumin and ginger; stir for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, potatoes, carrots and chopped cilantro.
Stir often until carrots are tender to bite, about 7 minutes.
Add flour and stir for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Then mix in eggs and bread crumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: red wine vinaigrette
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onion soup mix, sour cream, egg and bread crumbs together.
Roll into small balls and bake in oven at 320° until brown.
Put in crock-pot with 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 can water.
Heat until hot.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese at high speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add whipped topping, peanut butter, sugar and milk; beat well.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 5 hours before serving.
Garnish with peanuts, if desired.

title: tamal
directions: Thinly slice the vegetables.
Layer in casserole dish all vegetables, seasoning each layer.
Drizzle bacon drippings over top.
Bake (with lid) in oven about 2 hours at 300° or less.
Cook slowly.

title: mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crush wafers and add melted butter. Mix well with a fork and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread ice cream carefully onto crust.
Freeze 1 1/2 hours or until solid.
In a saucepan, cook cocoa, sugar, 1/3 cup cream and butter until it is smooth and boils.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool but do not let mixture get too hard to pour.
Pour sauce over frozen ice cream base.
Freeze at least 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, whip remaining cream with 2 tablespoons sugar until soft peaks form.
Add remaining vanilla and spread over pie.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: peanut butter sandwich filling
directions: Soften peanut butter and blend with pickle, bacon and mayonnaise. Yields 3/4 cup or makes 4 sandwiches.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream the cream cheese with the sugar.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and then chill.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
and onions;
drain off grease.
Slice potatoes and boil
for
minutes;
drain
off
water.
Spray casserole dish with
Pam.
Line
bottom
of dish with potatoes and then hamburger.
Mix
cheese, soup and Mrs. Dash together; pour over top of
potatoes and hamburger.
Mrs. Dash takes the place of salt and pepper.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: smothered steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides.
Place in casserole dish and cover with onion slices and soup.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks one at a time.
Mix soda and sour cream.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add flour. Beat the 6 egg whites; add 6 teaspoons of sugar, then fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tall boy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain excess fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 can of Tall Boy vegetable soup to the ground beef.
Do not dilute soup; add straight to ground beef. Mix and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Serve with creamed potatoes and rolls.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, cracker meal, eggs, pepper, garlic and onions. Use enough cracker meal so meat mixture is sticky. Make into small balls and fry until brown.

title: christmas toffee
directions: Spread nuts on greased 13 x 11-inch cookie sheet.
Combine margarine and sugar.
Melt and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until dark tan, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour toffee mixture over nuts.
Immediately place broken pieces of chocolate bars on hot mixture and spread with a knife.
Place in cool place or in refrigerator.
Take out when hard and break in pieces.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain. Spoon beef into 8-inch square baking dish, and top with sauce and cheese. Combine bisquick mix & eggs beat until smooth. Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken potato casserole
directions: Put frozen potatoes in well oiled 9 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken on top.
Blend soup with remaining ingredients except paprika.
Pour over the chicken and potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: plain cake
directions: Place cake mix, pudding, sugar, margarine and water in bowl and blend well.
Stir in eggs and mix.
Add oil, gradually beating all the while.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool and frost with confectioners sugar and milk mixture.
tags: lemon supreme cake mix or pineapple

title: bridget's aztec quiche
directions: Spread all of Jack and 1/2 of Cheddar cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle green chilies over cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs, half and half, salt and pepper together.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes uncovered or until eggs set.
Let stand before serving.

title: spoon bread
directions: To boiling water, add salt; slowly add corn meal, stirring constantly.
Add milk, eggs, butter and baking powder.
Bake in a buttered baking pan about 10 minutes in a hot oven.
Serve hot.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onions and celery in oleo until tender.
Add broccoli, soup and milk.
Heat.
Add cheese, rice, salt and pepper to taste. Cook until it thickens.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl with fork or spoon, mix flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
Add milk and salad oil all at once; stir until dough forms a ball.
With hand, knead dough in bowl 10 times or until smooth.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into balls.
Melt 1 bag chocolate chips and 3/4 stick paraffin wax.
Dip balls in this mixture and put on waxed paper.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to package directions.
Allow to cool.
In large saucepan, combine gelatin, cornstarch, spices and salt.
Stir in pumpkin and evaporated milk.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften gelatin.
Cook and stir for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir 1 cup hot mixture into eggs and return to saucepan with other mixture.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Equal.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover and chill 6 hours or overnight. Makes 8 servings.

title: onion mushroom meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: indonesian pork chops
directions: Trim chops.
Rub heated skillet with fat.
Season chops with salt and pepper. brown.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of fat. Combine peach juice, vinegar, brown sugar and seasonings.
Pour over chops.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Add peaches, peppers and pimiento.
Simmer covered five minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: apple-oatmeal crisp
directions: Spread apples in greased pan; set aside.
Mix oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon. Cut in margarine with fork.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until apples are tender.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cream together peanut butter and shortening.
Add sugar and milk and mix together.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients, then add peanuts.
Blend well. Serve with sliced apples.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes, put through sieve, grind garlic, peppers and onions.
Mix all other ingredients with this and cook until it is as thick as you want.
Put in quart jars and process in hot water bath for 40 minutes.
Total cooking time is about 3 hours.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together.
Make 3 holes (pockets).
In the 1st hole put baking soda and salt.
In the 2nd hole put vanilla and vinegar.
In the 3rd hole put oil.
Over all pour 1 cup of cold water.
Stir gently until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil or lard.

title: captain morgan pineapple nut cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or fluted pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until tester comes out clean.
Cool 25 minutes; remove from pan.
Finish cooling on wire rack.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Squeeze the lemon over the bowl with the juicer.
Add the cup of water and 3 teaspoons of sugar.
Mix.
Pour into glasses.
Add ice cubes.
Serves 2.

title: mexican rice
directions: Two cups raw rice is fried until golden brown.
Then add onions, green pepper and spices.
Mix together with rice for about 5 minutes.
Add water, tomato sauce and diced tomatoes.
Mix together (medium flame).
"DO NOT STIR WHILE COOKING; RICE WILL STICK TOGETHER".
Let cook about 15 to 20 minutes or until all water has evaporated.
Ready to serve and eat.

title: spaghetti meatballs and sauce
directions: Finely chop onion and lightly brown in saucepan in oil.
Add tomato paste with 3 paste cans of water and stewed tomatoes.
Let simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour, adding warm water to keep level.
Add salt, sugar, pepper, sweet basil, garlic salt (or garlic cloves), oregano and bay leaves.
Let simmer 1/2 hour and add warm water as needed.
Add meatballs.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Add to dry ingredients with nuts, vanilla and egg.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: tofu hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mash tofu with fork.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into little balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes. Can be stored in freezer.

title: gold rush punch
directions: Combine sugar, fruit juices and water in pitcher.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each egg.
Add milk alternately with sifted cake flour, beating until well mixed and smooth.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into well-greased tube cake pan. Bottom of pan should be lined with wax paper.
Place in cold oven set at 300° and bake until it leaves side of pan (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with onion 3 to 5 minutes and drain.
Melt butter in separate pan.
Add flour, salt and milk.
Heat until sauce is thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add cream cheese and stir until well blended.
Place broccoli and onions in a 2-quart greased casserole and add cooked sauce.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Cut Crisco into flour mixture.
Add water to make soft dough consistency.
Put berries in a 9 x 13-inch pan with sugar, water and margarine.
Bring to rolling boil.
Roll out 2/3 of the dough thin on floured waxed paper.
Cut into strips.
Drop into boiled berry mix.
Roll out remaining dough in strips.
Put on top of cobbler.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or golden brown.

title: party pizza
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Drain and crumble.
Cool bacon.
Mix bacon with cheeses, olives, onions and mayonnaise.
Place small amount on each slice of bread.
Place in oven until cheeses melt. Serve warm.
Great for brunch or midnight snacks.

title: salmonelle's
directions: Drain salmon and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Break apart salmon. Add egg and flour.
Add baking powder to reserved liquid; beat until foamy.
Pour into salmon mixture and stir until blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Pour water in saucepan and add butter.	Bring to a boil. Add the flour and stir until mixed. Remove from heat and let cool 2 minutes. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Spread mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool.

title: french fried new potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes.
Wash well and cut one strip of peel off around middle of potato.
Put in hot oil and cook until brown. Salt to taste.

title: moon cake
directions: Place 1 cup water and 1/2 cup margarine in a saucepan. Bring to boil. Add 1 cup flour all at once. Lower the flame and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat and cool a little while.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Cut slices of bread in four.
Spread each with mustard and top with ham cut to fit.
Place drained pineapple chunks on ham and top with Swiss cheese.
Cut to shape.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Serve at once.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack it in jars.
Add to each jar 2 buttons of garlic (slice or mash it slightly), 2 heads of dill and 1 hot pepper (Mexican chilian red).
Combine first ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over okra.
Seal immediately.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks; set egg white halves aside.
In a small bowl, use a fork to mash egg yolks.
Stir in salad dressing, mustard, pickles, onion and thyme.
Spoon egg yolk mixture evenly into egg white halves. Sprinkle tops of eggs with paprika.
Makes 12 appetizer servings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop green tomatoes; place in drainer.
Pour boiling water over tomatoes and let stand; drain.
Chop onions and peppers. Combine tomatoes, onions and peppers in a large canner.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to a simmer and cook for about 1 hour.
Pack in cleaned jars; seal with canning lid and process for 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 to 9 pints.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together beans, sugar and mustard. Crumble bacon and add to beans. Add some bacon grease to taste. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9 baking dish.

title: mim's seafood bisque
directions: Heat soups and milk.
Add cream cheese and sherry.
Add seafood and enjoy.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and nuts. Mix well. Add melted oleo and orange juice. Blend well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Chill until firm.

title: oven barbecued steaks
directions: Heat oven to 350° (medium).
Cut steak into 10 equal portions. Pour oil into skillet.
Brown each piece of steak on both sides. Transfer steaks to a roasting pan.
Add onions to oil in skillet and brown lightly.
Add rest of ingredients to make a barbecue sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over steaks in pan. Cover.
Bake 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.

title: peanut banana muffins
directions: Combine first four ingredients in bowl and make a well in center.
Combine rest of ingredients and beat at medium speed until blended.
Then add to flour mixture and stir just to moisten.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together in large container.
Makes lots.
To serve, place 1/4 cup of mix in mug.
Add boiling water.
Stir and enjoy.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes a great Christmas gift!
Give small amounts in colorful containers with directions attached.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Unwrap tamales cut crosswise into 1/2 inch slices.
Line 11/2 qt. casserole with half tamales slices.
Spread half chili over top.
Cover with half of the onions hen half of chips and half of cheese.
Repeat except for the cheese.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 large servings.

title: instant pudding cookies
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each ball slightly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.
(Lemon is very good.)

title: quick caramel pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and beaten egg.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat until smooth; add vanilla and butter.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown; cool in refrigerator until served.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Combine cheese, soup, milk, catsup and meat.
Pour into casserole and bake 10 minutes at 375°. Remove from oven; place biscuits on top and bake 15 to 18 minutes until biscuits are brown.

title: baked fish cordon blue
directions: Thaw fillets if frozen.
Place 1 slice each of ham and cheese in center of each fillet.
Cut to fit.
Sprinkle with grated orange rind and white pepper.
Roll into pinwheels and secure with toothpicks.
Gently dip roll in beaten egg; coat with bread crumbs.
Place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: chocolate chip bread pudding
directions: Combine bread cubes and 1/4 cup chocolate chips in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In a separate bowl, combine beaten eggs, sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour mixture over bread.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over this. Place casserole dish in a pan of water and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: christmas roll cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and vanilla.
Dissolve sugar.
Add dates and beaten egg.
Cook 10 minutes on medium heat.
Cool and add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls, then in coconut. Refrigerate or seal tightly.
Yield: 40 small balls.

title: luscious lemon dessert
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Prepare 2 packages pudding, using only 3 cup milk.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Season chicken breasts.
Place chicken breasts in large pot, along with bell pepper, celery and onion.
Add water in pot until chicken breasts are covered.
Let cook for about 4 hours, until breasts are tender (falling off bone).
Chop breasts into small pieces.
Add mustard, relish and mayonnaise to taste.
Add eggs (chopped also into small pieces).
Stir; ready to serve.

title: grandma simons' broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, rice, soup, water, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Combine and bake in greased casserole, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift
together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the vanilla, vinegar, oil and cold water; blend until moist, then beat at medium
speed
with an electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the Cheese Filling.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts; reserve 2 cups of broth.
Remove chicken from bone and tear into bite size pieces.
Place in 3-quart baking dish.
Combine soups and 1 cup of broth; pour over chicken.
Mix margarine and remaining 1 cup of broth; stir in stuffing.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bombay tuna
directions: In medium bowl, combine tuna, apple, celery, green onion, almonds and currants.
Stir in mayonnaise, chutney, mustard and curry powder.
Refrigerate.
Great for summertime entertaining!

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Put drained pineapple in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle flour/sugar mixture on top.
Then cover with cheese.
Mix crushed crackers with melted butter and layer on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: collards a la italiana
directions: Heat oil and add onion.
Cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes longer.
Season with salt and pepper and marjoram.
Add collards.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir frequently and add juice of tomatoes or water to keep moist.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: souperior italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done. Makes about 8 servings.
Also, may use Lipton "Recipe Secrets" beefy onion soup mix instead of onion or Italian herb.

title: honey-without the bees
directions: Put clovers and rose petals in colander; wash and drain.
In large heavy kettle, place all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat to low and cook another 5 minutes, stirring constantly; strain.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 8 jars.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Mix sugar, eggs, salt and dates in with butter. Cook until thick and mash the dates while cooking (about 10 to 15 minutes). Remove from heat. Add pecans and vanilla. Add Rice Krispies. Mix well. Spoon out and roll into a ball about an inch in diameter. Roll in coconut.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Put into a buttered baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake in a 400° oven about 20 minutes or until done.

title: granola bars
directions: Stir and heat honey and peanut butter until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, raisins and carrots; mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Saute onion; stir in flour and milk.
Add cheese.
Mix with drained spinach.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: swiss steak
directions: Tenderize steak.
Beat egg and milk.
Combine with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Cut steak into serving portions.
Preheat vegetable oil on medium.
Dip steak in flour, egg mixture and bread crumbs.
Brown both sides of steak until golden brown.
Pour 3/4 can of gravy in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place single layer steak on gravy in pan.
Saute mushrooms in leftover oil and bread crumbs.
Place mushrooms on top of steak.
Pour remaining gravy over steak and mushrooms.
Cover with foil.
Cook
2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Add berries, eggs and oil.
Mix well and pour into 3 well-greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans or 1 large and 1 small bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk fried chicken and biscuits
directions: Place chicken into bowl.
Pour buttermilk over; marinate for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: single serving pizza
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup pizza sauce.
Cut English muffins, put on cookie sheet, cut side down. Brown lightly.
Turn muffins, cut side up, and spread with reserved pizza sauce, covering the edges.
Divide equal portions of the meat mixture onto each muffin and smooth to cover. Sprinkle the tops with grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Cut bread
into
1-inch slices.
Remove crust from each slice. Heat
oil in 12-inch Dutch oven.
Mix eggs, nutmeg and salt in large bowl.
Whip until eggs are frothy.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Deep
fry
until	golden	brown.	Sprinkle
with powdered sugar.

title: aunt dina's chili pie casserole
directions: Place 2 cups of corn chips in 2 quart baking dish or 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish.
Arrange onion and 1/2 cup grated cheese on chips. Pour chili over.
Then top with remaining corn chips and 1/2 cup cheese.
Place olives on top or garnish with olives after baking. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
If you make this dish earlier in the day and have it refrigerated it will take longer to heat.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, shortening, sugar and salt with pastry blender. Beat the egg.
Add the water and vinegar to the egg and mix well. Combine the two mixtures, a little at a time, until all the dry ingredients are moist.
Mold together with your hands.
Makes 2 double crust 9-inch pies and one 9-inch shell.
May keep in refrigerator up to 1 week.
May freeze.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take out while still soft.
M&M's, chocolate chips, nuts, etc., may be added as desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine
sugar,
flour and salt.
Blend in milk and egg yolks. Combine
flour mixture with milk mixture.
Cook on top of double boiler on medium heat until thickened.
Add vanilla. Pour into serving bowl in layers, then add bananas and wafers. Alternate. End
with
wafers.
Can
top with meringue.
If so bake until golden brown.

title: torre's cake
directions: Combine butter, flour and crushed almonds and mix well.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown. Cool.

title: sun-drenched chicken breasts
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil and brown chicken over medium heat for 10 minutes, turning once; drain.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
In same skillet, add wine and boil 2 minutes, stirring brown bits from bottom of skillet.
Stir in tomato and golden herb with lemon soup mix, blended with water.
Return chicken to skillet.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Top with olives and parsley.
Serve, if desired, over hot cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together the quick oats and boiling water and set aside. Cream together sugars, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Add oatmeal and mix well. Beat at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: overnight scalloped chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, milk and cheese.
Add chicken or turkey, macaroni and eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted margarine. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Toss the bread crumbs with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown. Yield:
12 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans in a small bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except onion) and toss with beans.
Garnish with onion rings.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot bars
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add carrots and dry ingredients, alternating; mix. Add coconut.
Bake 20 minutes at 325° in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Sift several cups of flour (3 to 4 cups) into large mixing bowl.
Add butter to sugar into well made in center of sifted flour; cream.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Work enough flour into mixture to make dough stiff enough to roll and cut.
Place cookies on cookie sheet and bake until as brown as desired.
Bake at about 350°.

title: glazed beets in orange sauce
directions: Combine cornstarch and beet juice.
Mix well.
Stir in orange juice, lemon juice, salt and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until clear and thickened.
Add sugars and beets.
Cook for 5 minutes and add butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with orange peel.
Serve hot.

title: smoky bean dip
directions: Rinse and drain chickpeas.
Puree with chopped green chiles, barbecue sauce, ground cumin and minced garlic.
Cover and chill at least 1 day for best flavor.

title: skillet salad
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cover. Simmer for 10 to 12 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp. Ingredients may be prepared early in day and mixed together in skillet 15 minutes before dinner.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican crock-pot
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Drain meat.
Put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Mix together, stirring well.
Turn crock-pot on low.
Simmer all day.
Add tortilla chips as a side dish.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt. Cook for 8 minutes in microwave on High. Stir well after 4 minutes. After the 8 minutes, stir in the butter and vanilla; cook for 2 more minutes on High in microwave. Add the baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour the mixture onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Spread the mixture out until very thin. After it has cooled, break into small pieces and store in an airtight container. Makes about 1 pound. You have to keep it hidden if you want some for yourself.

title: caramel marshmallow krispies
directions: Melt oleo, milk and caramels.
Dip marshmallows in caramel sauce.
Roll in Rice Krispies.
Store, uncovered.
Makes large batch.

title: super loaf
directions: Stir everything together.
Pour into a large loaf pan and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: May add food color if you desire.

title: awesome apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spread half of apples into an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Stir brown sugar into melted margarine.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Combine with sugar and margarine and mix well.
Crumble half of oatmeal mix over apples in pan.
Cover with rest of apple slices.
Crumble remaining mixture over top of pan.
Pour on orange juice.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Pour in a large pot with all ingredients except potatoes and carrots.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Put in carrots.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook for another 20 minutes or until done.

title: myrtle's pound cake
directions: Cream butter,
Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix baking powder with flour;
add to cake mixture.
Add milk and flavorings.
Pour into
a
greased and lightly floured tube pan and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325° or 300°.

title: cheesy tuna 'n rice muffinlettes
directions: Combine rice, cheese, tuna, olives, onion, parsley and Season-All.
Stir in eggs and milk, mixing thoroughly.
Spray 6 muffin cups with Pam.
Divide rice mixture evenly among cups. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Loosen with spatula and arrange on serving plate.
Serve with Tangy Butter Sauce.
Makes 6.

title: fettucine, peas and mushrooms
directions: In large pot, boil water.
Add salt, oil and fettucine.
Cook al dente.
Drain.
Cook peas until tender (if can hot).
Saute mushrooms in butter and cream until tender.
Toss with cheese, peas and fettucine.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese, flour and eggs.
Mix well; add parsley, onion and garlic powder.
Put in casserole with onion rings on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: veal and mushrooms in white wine sauce
directions: Pound veal into 1/4-inch thickness.
Rub with garlic, then sprinkle with flour. Saute veal in butter until brown. Add mushrooms, wine and salt.
Cook on low heat for about 15 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Top with fresh parsley.

title: main meal hominy salad
directions: Rinse hominy and drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill well.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with tomato wedges.

title: chocolate coconutty delights
directions: Note:
To make drizzling with chocolate easier, put thin melted mixture in a plastic bag.
Snip off a corner of the bag and drizzle chocolate coating through the hole.

title: red hot (cinnamon) cucumber pickles
directions: *The kind that's red all the way through.
The ones with white insides will make a cloudy look.

title: crunchy cheeseroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add soups, green pepper and pimento.
Mix.

title: hurry up pie
directions: Mix the milk and lemon juice; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients well.
Fill 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Coarsely crush cookies and reserve 1/4 cup crumbs.
To remaining crumbs, add melted butter and blend well.
Press crumb mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with powdered sugar and half thawed whipped topping.
Spread over crumb layer in pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker ice cream sandwiches
directions: Crush 4 graham crackers.
Arrange 4 of the remaining crackers on work surface.
Spread chocolate evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of crumbs on each cracker and press gently into chocolate.
Arrange remaining 4 crackers on baking sheet.
Top each with 1/2 cup of ice milk.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on ice milk.
Top with coated crackers, chocolate side down.
Freeze 30 minutes or until firm.
Wrap and keep frozen until served.

title: pickled beets
directions: Prepare beets by boiling for approximately 20 minutes with 3 inch of top and roots still on.
Drain and place in cold water. Slip skins off; trim top and roots.
If small, leave whole.
If not, slice and place in clean jars.

title: brownies
directions: You make up at home and for Thanksgiving dinner.
Get a brown potato that is white inside.
Carve it out and throw away the peelings.
Smash it good and put some milk in it.
(I think that's how you make it.)

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake batter to directions.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Beat sugar and cream cheese.
Melt butter and pour into sugar mixture.
Pour over your cake.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with cherries or strawberries.

title: crust for peach cobbler
directions: Stir and mix well.
Drop on top of fruit mixture in baking dish.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°, or until brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour and seasoning mixture.
Fry in hot oil until lightly browned on both sides.
When all steak has been browned, place in skillet, cover with water and tomato sauce and season to taste.
Cover and simmer over medium heat for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add onion slices for extra flavor before you cover and simmer.

title: beanie weanies
directions: Melt
Crisco
in pan.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until soft.
Add
brown sugar, ketchup, vinegar, dry mustard, salt
and pepper.
Simmer
until
sugar
is
dissolved.
Pour mixture over hot dogs, butter beans, kidney beans and pork and beans.
Stir until well coated.
Pour into a large dish, cover and cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy cheese potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine cheeses, butter, onion (sauteed first), sour cream, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Add flour; stir until sauce is creamy and smooth.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes; sprinkle with salts.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Sprinkle cooked bacon on top.
Cook in oven at 325° for about 10 minutes, or until bubbly and brown.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, flour and eggs.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Makes two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet chicken risotto
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown chicken in hot oil for about 15 minutes.
Remove chicken and drain all but 2 tablespoons fat from skillet.
Add rice, onion, salt and poultry seasoning to skillet. Cook and stir until rice is lightly browned.
Add mushrooms, carrots and water.
Place chicken atop rice mixture.
Season chicken with additional salt and pepper.

title: homemade lasagne
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Spread 1 cup of meat sauce into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/4 of the lasagne, 1/3 of the Ricotta mixture and 1 cup meat sauce and repeat twice.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Top layer should be Mozzarella.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute the onion, celery, and bell pepper in the garlic butter until vegetables are tender. Sprinkle flour over the vegetables and stir.

Cook until flour is no longer white. Watch it carefully to avoid burning. Add shrimp and cook just until shrimp turn pink. Add tomato paste, stewed tomatoes, water, salt, Worcestershire and Tabasco. Cook over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all and chill.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine and marshmallows together.
Add remaining ingredients separately and mix well.
Press in container of your choice.
Put in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon strips; leave grease drippings in pan.
Remove bacon.
Add diced onion and brown.
Add green beans (drain 1/2 the can).
Add tomatoes, chopped; simmer.
Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer.
Crumble bacon strips and sprinkle over the green beans.

title: jade delight
directions: Blend all ingredients except oil in blender at high speed. Add oil and blend until well emulsified.
For a milder version omit the crushed red pepper.

title: zucchini and ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and celery.
Remove from pan; drain off fat.
I rinse mine in water and drain.
In same skillet, add 1 tablespoon oleo and brown zucchini.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of ground beef and zucchini.
Sprinkle each layer of meat and zucchini with salt and pepper (easy on salt).
In small dish, stir tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over casserole.
Add cheese on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: toffee butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add sugar, syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally to hard crack stage (300°). (Watch carefully after 280°.)
Quickly stir in chopped nuts.

title: caramel cluster
directions: Heat margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until melted.
Stir in sugar.
Stir frequently with wooden spoon, 4 to 5 minutes while mixture melts and begins to turn a golden color. Continue cooking 1 to 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
(Do not overcook; mixture will go from granular to smooth and margarine and sugar may begin to separate.)
Remove from heat.
Quickly add cereal and mix until coated; immediately spread on cookie sheet. Cool.
Break into bite-size pieces.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage (drain).
Melt cheese.
Combine tomatoes and cheese with sausage.
Serve with corn chips.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and lay margarine sticks on top.
Do not stir.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.
Do not double this recipe.

title: fun bubbles galore
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature before using, about 4 hours.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat with diced onion; add celery.
Cook, covered. Simmer until meat is done.
Add bouillon cubes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir together.
Serve over cooked rice.
Sprinkle with chop suey noodles.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and margarine; cream together for 6 minutes (no longer).
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter or chocolate chips.
Mix well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add food coloring and cocoa. Mix salt and vanilla with buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternating with flour.
Mix soda and vinegar and fold in; do not beat.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese rings
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix grated cheese and margarine together.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to cheese mixture a little at a time.
Using star disc of cookie press, press out onto wax paper in a long stream.
Cut with knife in approximately 2-inch strips. Turn these to form a ring and press together.
This recipe makes approximately 25 dozen rings.

title: alpine pantry bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove, cool and crumble or chop.
Cook onions in bacon fat until tender.
Add brown sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar; saute for 2 minutes.
Add all beans and bacon.
Stir in catsup.
Mix well; cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or longer.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken italian
directions: Cover chicken and potatoes with oil, garlic salt, and salt. Add tomato sauce, oregano, and cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: fresh vegetable salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover; refrigerate 1 hour. Serve with chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: texas chili
directions: Heat vegetable oil in skillet.
Add beef cubes and brown on all sides.
Remove and set aside.
Cook onion in oil from meat until tender.
Add beef.
Combine spices and stir in to beef mixture.
Add beer, broth and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Combine flour and water.
Slowly stir into chili.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except spareribs.
Brown ribs over medium-high heat in a large skillet.
Pour sauce over ribs. Cook, covered, until sauce thickens a little and meat is done. Uncover and cook until sauce thickens and is sticky.

title: cauliflower-broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed; drain.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Sprinkle onion, pimento and cheese over vegetables.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with crackers and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick spinach dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve with potato chips or fresh vegetables.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.
Preparation time is 15 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hunter veal
directions: Optional:
Serve with biscuits or over noodles.

title: french bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. In large bowl, dissolve sugar and salt in 1 cup warm water.
Add shortening and yeast. Add flour and mix well with wooden spoon.
Work dough with spoon at 10 minute intervals five times.
Turn dough on floured board into 2 balls.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Roll each ball into 12 x 9-inches, then roll as for jelly roll.
Place on greased baking sheet and score 6 times.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours (covered). Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: daddy's chili
directions: Brown meat.
Combine all ingredients in pot and simmer several hours.
You may need to add more chili powder to suit your taste.

title: steak topping
directions: Slice mushrooms lengthwise (leave button or small ones whole). Slice onion into rings.
In medium skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic powder, seasoned salt and pepper and stir.
Add mushrooms, onion rings and beer or wine.
Cover. Simmer until juice is fairly thick.
Pour over sirloin (or other kind) steak.

title: red punch
directions: Mix each package Kool-Aid with 2 cups sugar each.
Mix all other ingredients, except ginger ale, in a dish pan.
Pour in 2 gallon jugs and add enough water to fill.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale (cooled) last, directly into punch bowl.

title: "i don't feel like cooking" beef and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan and bake for 1 hour.
This is delicious and low in fat (but high in sodium).

title: rosh hashana sweet potato-praline casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Beat eggs in a large bowl. Stir in potatoes. Mash smoothly. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Spread evenly in baking dish.

title: lime pineapple cream salad
directions: Cream together jello and cream cheese.
Pour over this mixture hot water and stir until smooth.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Chill until set.
Serve with lettuce and mayonnaise.

title: "96" apricot bavarian
directions: Dissolve apricot gelatin in boiling water.
Add nectar.
Let cool.
Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Add 1 1/2 cartons Cool Whip in gelatin mix.
Blend well.
Using 10-inch tube pan, put layer of cake, gelatin mixture and continue, ending with gelatin mix.
Cover and put in refrigerator for at least 6 hours.
Unmold on cake plate and ice with remaining Cool Whip and garnish with halves of apricots.
Serves 12.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Spray a baking dish lightly with cooking spray.
Place 1/2 bag of tortillas on bottom of pan.
On top of tortillas, spread chili.
On top of chili, add cheeses.
On top of cheeses, add diced vegetables.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake approximately 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins and water for 5 minutes, then add sugar, flour and vinegar.
Stir all the time.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic french bread
directions: Place butter and garlic in saucepan and bring to a simmer, constantly stirring.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Spoon liquid on bread.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Add cheese and broil in oven to taste/sight.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order given.
Form a ball, using about a teaspoon.
Press lightly on cookie sheet with fork. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bundle burgers
directions: In medium saucepan, cook stuffing according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, mix the hamburger, eggs and bread crumbs.
Divide hamburger mix like you were making hamburger patties.
Flatten each patty out.
Put a scoop of stuffing in middle, then fold the hamburger up around it and make a little bundle.
Place in 9 x 11 baking pan.
Mix the soup and milk together in small bowl.
Pour over the bundles of hamburger.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine and saute carrots, celery and onion.
Add broth and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add soup, cheese and seasonings. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and sherry, if desired. Blend well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: smothered hamburger steaks
directions: Season hamburger with salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 large patties and brown in large skillet.
Mix brown gravy mix with water it calls for plus 1/2 cup extra and bring to boil according to directions.
Drain off grease from hamburgers.
Pour gravy over hamburgers.
Slice onion.
Place over burgers.
Bring to boil. Cover pan and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: coconut chocolate pie
directions: Toast coconut.
Mix with melted butter and chocolate.
Press into a pie shell as for a crust.
Chill.
Spread with softened ice cream.
Chill and serve in slices.

title: diabetic chocolate pie
directions: Place in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cook over low heat slowly. When thickened, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put in pie shell which has already been baked.

title: creamsicle dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare pudding, using 2 cups cold milk.
Fold mandarin oranges, thickened jello and 1 cup whipped topping into pudding.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Use either boneless chicken breast (cooked), or diced frozen chicken.

title: hearty meatball stew
directions: Shape sausage into balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs in oil, carefully turning to brown evenly.
Remove meatballs from skillet.
Reserve 2 tablespoons meat drippings in skillet; stir in flour and pepper. Gradually add 1 cup water and chicken broth. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add carrots, celery, onion and meatballs.
Simmer uncovered 20 to 30 minutes.
Add corn; heat thoroughly.
In large saucepan, heat 2 cups water to boiling; add cabbage.
Cover and cook 8 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Arrange cabbage on serving platter surrounding stew.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in a bowl and beat with mixer. Pour mixture into ice cream freezer and add condensed milk and stir well. Add whole milk to fill line on can and stir. Put can in ice cream freezer and alternate layers of ice and rock salt. Churn until firm. Store remaining ice cream in freezer.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and let marinate overnight.
You can add or take away whatever you want.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Crumble bread in milk; add salt and pepper to meat.
Form into medium balls; place them in a small casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the meat balls.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: 15 minute beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the meat.
Add water and soups.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Blend sour cream and flour and add to the meat.
Cook and stir until thick.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix
above ingredients and cook moderately high.
Stir. Peanuts will
begin
to
pop
and
turn light brown around the edges when
done.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Pour
immediately onto buttered cookie sheet.
Take up as soon as brittle will break and loosen from sheet.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Trim bread; cut in half.
Mix cream cheese and sausage. Spread on bread; roll
up.
Wrap
with slice of bacon;
secure with toothpick.
Bake on rack at 350° until brown.

title: not the same old chicken
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish, arrange chicken with thickest, meaty pieces to outside edges of dish.
In small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, onion soup mix, dressing and preserves. Spread over chicken, coating each piece.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave at High 18 to 22 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving, so chicken absorbs flavor of sauce.
Serve with rice, if desired. Makes about 4 servings.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix by hand.
If they do not hold together, add 1 small jar of regular peanut butter.
Roll into balls; refrigerate overnight.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with 2 Chronicles 9:9 (spices).
Mix like any fruit cake.
Put in lined tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: miracle chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and
pepper.
Brown quickly in a little oil and place in a
baking dish.
Combine maple syrup and ketchup.
Pour this mixture
over
chicken.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Then
just
sit back and wait for the compliments.

title: apple peekaboo
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix yellow cake mix to package directions.
Pour cake mix into pan.
Mix apples and sugar; pour over cake mix.
Pour pint of cream over top.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Brown beef in small amount of fat. Mix in rest of ingredients, except topping. Spread in pastry-lined pie pan. Spread Cheese Topping over filling.
Bake about 30 minutes. Serve with sauce. (Sauce is remaining 4 ounces tomato sauce and 4 ounces chili sauce.)

title: sugar-free fat-free banana bread
directions: Beat together until fluffy, juice, bananas, eggs and flavorings.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Mix all until just blended.
Add optional nuts or raisins or fruit bits.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes approximately.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Note:
This recipe is quick and great for diets!

title: congealed jello and fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and let them melt and puff up.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into dish approximately 9 x 9-inch and chill.

title: vanilla ice cream(makes 4 quarts)
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture thickens.
Add condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix and chill 2 hours before freezing.

title: chicken pot pie i
directions: Mix soup, milk, veggies, salt and pepper to taste. Layer chicken in pie crust, then pour soup and veggies over top of chicken. Mix a little bit, then cover with pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in buttered casserole dish at 250° for 2 hours until knife in center comes out fairly clean.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter sweet potatoes.
Add water and cook until tender in saucepan.
Place in baking dish with brown sugar, white syrup and butter.
Put into oven and let cook 20 minutes at 350°. Then put marshmallows on top and let brown slightly.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserve 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Top with reserved grated cheese.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake approximately 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Great for apples, pear slices and oranges too.

title: one pot meal
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low heat four to nine hours.
This can also be made in oven in a covered casserole.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pears with creme de menthe
directions: In a large bowl, place pear halves.
Reserve the juice; add creme de menthe to individual taste.
Blend carefully; pour over pears.
Refrigerate until very cold.
Just before serving, add nuts and/or cherries.
Use red or green to suit the occasion!

title: fuzzy navel milkshake
directions: Combine ice cream, peaches and orange juice in blender.
Blend only until mixed and don't worry about lumps of unblended peaches. Pour into tall glasses and garnish with strawberries.
Makes 2 tall drinks.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Put cookie in foil baking cup.
Fill 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool and put pie filling on top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour with salt also.
Then add eggs and add milk slowly.
Then add vanilla.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Melt butter; add garlic, cream and cheese.
Heat until thickened while stirring constantly.
Add broccoli, mushrooms and noodles.
Will thicken upon standing.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and spices; boil 10 minutes.
Cook peaches until tender in boiling syrup, a few at a time.
Pack in jars and fill with boiling syrup and seal.

title: mark's new york chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Prepare pudding, using entire quart of milk.
Cover bottom of a large glass trifle bowl with syrup.
Break 1 cake layer into pieces and place on top of syrup.
