Spread 1/2 pudding mixture over cake pieces.
Spread 1/2 Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle candy pieces over Cool Whip. Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon poke cake
directions: Bake cake according to package. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. When cool, poke holes in top of cake with fork. Pour 7-Up evenly over top.

title: baked corn with sour cream
directions: Saute onion in butter in large skillet.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add sour cream gradually, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil; add corn.
Cook until heated through.
Fold in half the bacon.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with parsley and remaining bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut almond macaroons
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugars; mix well.
Work in almond paste until mixture resembles fine bread crumbs.
Stir in salt, vanilla, cocoa and coconut; mix well.
Add egg whites, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Line cookie sheet with brown paper.
Drop or put through super shooter; make small mounds, 1 1/2 inches in size.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 325° or until lightly colored.
Cool by placing brown paper on damp towel; cookies will peel off easily.
Place in airtight container so cookies remain chewy.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, juice and seasonings; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Reserve salad dressing mixture; place chicken, skin side up, on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes, brushing occasionally with salad dressing mixture.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mom's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in tightly covered container.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Add the chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip caramels in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: cinnamon apple mold salad
directions: Place candies and water in saucepan and cook over medium heat until candies are melted.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot liquid.
Let cool slightly and then add applesauce, mixing well. Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, 1/2 of oregano, 1/2 of onions and peppers, pinch of garlic and dash of black pepper.
Make into meatballs. Mix remainder of ingredients into a large saucepan.
Put in meatballs and simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Let cool and skim off fat that rises to the top.
Can be refrigerated and frozen for future use several days later.

title: date balls
directions: Cook oleomargarine, sugar and dates in top of double boiler for 8 minutes; stir often.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies; mix well. Cool mixture for about 45 minutes and then roll into balls (about the size of a large marble).
Roll date balls lightly in confectioners sugar.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water, corn syrup and cornstarch until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add strawberry jello powder.
Remove from heat and cool.
Place 1 quart fresh strawberries in baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Pour cooled sauce over berries.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: pear pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust and fill with pears. Mix 1/4 c. sugar, salt, cornstarch, lemon rind and juice together. Spread over pears. Mix remaining ingredients together with a fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over pears. Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all of this together and pour in churn.
Makes 4 quarts of homemade ice cream. Tastes like a Wendy's frosty!

title: apple raisin muffins
directions: Grease twelve 3 1/2 to 4 oz. muffin cups.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat oil and sugar with an electric beater for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat 1 minute.
In another bowl, stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to oil mixture.
Stir just to combine.
Stir in apples, raisins and walnuts.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes before removing muffins from cups.
Finish cooling on rack.
Muffins freeze well.

title: crock-pot chicken dressing
directions: Melt margarine and crumble cornbread. Mix all except chicken. Add chicken last. Cook dressing and chicken in crock pot on HIGH for 45 minutes. Stir and continue to cook on LOW for 4 hours.

title: best chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Add ground beef and saute until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain and add kidney beans.
Add tomatoes and paste.
Add garlic, salt and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in some of the reserved liquid if you like and make to desired consistency.

title: carolyn's bologna
directions: Mix well.
Shape into 4 rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kolbasi and sauerkraut
directions: Bake kolbasi in 325° oven for 1 hour in pan with water to cover.
Thoroughly rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Place in part with 2 whole onions and salt pork; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to cover; simmer 45 minutes.
When kolbasi is cooked, drain and cut into 4-inch pieces.
Add to sauerkraut and continue cooking for 30 minutes.
Brown flour in bacon fat.
When golden brown, add to kolbasi and sauerkraut and mix thoroughly.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Ingredients must be very finely chopped.
Mix all together. Serve as a vegetable or cracker dip or wonderful as a small sandwich filling.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl.

title: four day coconut cake(gordon robinson's favorite)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions.
Bake two 9-inch layers.
Let cool overnight.
Then, separate two layers into four layers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, water, Karo syrup and butter, then add salt, peanuts and continue to boil to 290°.
Remove from heat, sift in soda and vanilla and stir well.
Pour thin onto buttered cookie sheet.
When cold, break into pieces.
Put into tight container for keeping.

title: artichoke torte
directions: Saute onions and parsley in oil from 2 jars of artichokes. Mix eggs, cheese, crackers, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce until blended smooth.
Mix with onions and parsley. Cut up artichokes and add to mixture. Grease an oblong baking dish and fill with mixture. Bake at 325°
for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold as an appetizer or vegetable.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Place each chicken breast half on a sheet of waxed paper; flatten to 1/2-inch thickness using a meat mallet.
Chop ham and Swiss cheese; add minced parsley and pepper to ham and cheese. Mix well.

title: broiled shrimp and scallops
directions: In a large bowl combine oil, garlic, parsley, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and scallops to mixture; mix well until coated.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat in a 3-quart saucepot until it loses its red color; drain off fat.
Add vegetables except green beans and corn, hot chili beans, tomatoes, consomme, water, Worcestershire, chili powder and spices.
Cover and bring to boil; simmer 40 minutes so vegetables are tender and flavors mingle.
Add thawed green beans and corn; simmer another 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole *
directions: Cook squash and mash.
Mix squash and melted margarine.
Mix dry ingredients with squash and margarine.
Beat eggs and Coffee Rich and pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and butter together and roll into small balls.
Double boil chocolate chips and paraffin wax until both are melted.
Put toothpicks in balls and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper and dry.
Chill, then serve.
Makes 60 Buckeyes approximately.

title: skier's sausage
directions: Brown sausage and cut each link in half.
Drain well.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine meat and apples and put into casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, lemon juice and sugar. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour over it.
Let set up for at least an hour in refrigerator before eating it.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine all ingredients, then fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle each cup with nutmeg.

title: cream caramelle
directions: Put sugar in saucepan and melt at medium heat.
Then pour it into an aluminum mold, trying to cover all the sides of mold while sugar is hot.
Let it cool.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour into mold.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Spread evenly on bottom of prepared pastry shell.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate with margarine.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs with remaining sweetened condensed milk, water, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake 35 minutes or until center is set. Cool; chill and refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep baking dish.
Make batter of sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: quick and easy low-fat chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken for about 1 hour; cool and separate into small pieces.
(This can be done ahead of time and placed in the refrigerator.)
Cut flour tortillas into strips and strips into small dumplings.
Place tortillas into chicken broth and add chicken; simmer until liquid is absorbed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: candy pickles
directions: Day 1:
Peel 15 large cucumbers.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Remove center for ring.
Put in lime water (8 1/2 quarts water, 2 cups lime).
Let stand 24 hours.
Stir occasionally as lime settles.

title: shoney's style strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water. Cook until thick. Stir in jello; cool completely. Pour over berries. Put in pie shell and top with whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cook cake at 350° until pulls away from edges.

title: my first meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, shape into loaf and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Mix water and 1/4 cup sugar, then shake yeast on top and let stand while mixing other ingredients (don't stir yeast).
Cream Crisco and 1/4 cup sugar.
Then add well beaten egg whites to Crisco and sugar.
Mix well yeast mixture with Crisco mixture, then add enough of the flour for a thin batter.
Mix with electric mixer.
Work in the extra flour gradually (by hand).
The dough should be stiff enough until it doesn't stick to floured board or hands.

title: waldorf chicken sandwich
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve on whole grain bread.
Makes 3 servings.

title: roasted pepper salad(12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place peppers on baking sheet and roast until skins are black and peppers are soft, about 30 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Peel off skin.
Cut peppers in half and discard stem and seeds; slice peppers thinly.
Transfer to large serving bowl (preferably glass).

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown butter and flour. Add onion, celery and pepper.
Saute until light brown. Add okra and cook until okra is not ropey. Stir often.
Add tomatoes, hot water, bay leaves, garlic and crab meat, in that order. Simmer for 30 minutes. Add shrimp, oysters, green onions and parsley.
Season to taste. Simmer 1 hour and serve over rice.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place cut up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine.
Add to flour and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine Bisquick and eggs, adding milk until smooth.
Line casserole dish with meat.
Pour Bisquick mixture over meat and sprinkle with cheese.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix sugar and melted oleo well.
Add flour and eggs; mix well. Add vanilla and pecans and mix well.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and cool completely before cutting into squares.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: mah-fry chicken(chinese chicken)
directions: Marinate cut up chicken for 1 to 2 hours in sauce made from the sugar, ginger powder, garlic salt, soy sauce, funju and egg. Drain chicken; dip in flour and fry in deep fat.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in yeast mixture, oil and buttermilk.
(If using shortening, cut into dry ingredients to resemble coarse cornmeal before adding yeast mixture and buttermilk.)
Keep dough in refrigerator up to two weeks.

title: no-cook chow-chow
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients fine; measure after chopping.
Mix salt, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over chopped vegetables.
Let stand 6 hours.
Pour into small jars.
Do not deep seal.

title: baked egg cups
directions: Cook bacon until done, but not crisp.
Generously grease 12 muffin or popover cups.
Line sides with bacon.
Combine crumbs with margarine.
Place 1 tablespoon of crumbs in bottom of each cup.
Carefully place 1 raw egg in each cup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over eggs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until eggs reach stage you prefer.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Stir oil, sugar, pepper and vinegar together; let set 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Mix rest of ingredients and serve on a lettuce leaf.
Put dressing on just before serving.

title: barbecue in a pocket
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Mix in barbecue sauce; heat.
Roll out crescent rolls, using 4 to make square on baking sheet.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on rolled rolls and spoon meat to within 1 inch of edge.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and cover with other 4 rolls.
(Rolled and squared.)
Seal edges and brown.
Serve with favorite vegetable and garnish with fruit.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: About
hours
before
serving,
grease
1-quart casserole; set aside.
In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, beat milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs until well mixed; add bread, raisins and butter.
Toss
until
bread is well coated. Sprinkle mixture lightly
with
cinnamon.
Bake
in
preheated 300° oven for 55 to 60 minutes, until knife inserted in center of pudding comes out clean.
If
you like, serve with half and half. Makes 4 servings.

title: one rise monkey bread
directions: Using solid shortening or margarine, grease a 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon dill.
Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup and level off.
In a large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups flour and the next 6 ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in the remaining 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour.
On a floured surface, knead dough until smooth, about 1 minute.
Press or roll to a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Using a pastry wheel or sharp knife, cut dough into diamond shape pieces by cutting 1 1/2 to 2-inch strips.
Dip each piece in melted butter and layer in prepared pan.
Sprinkle each layer with 1/2 teaspoon dill weed. Cover and let rise in a warm place until light and doubled in size (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until deep golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes before turning out.

title: keir's famous horseshoes
directions: Fry turkey in pan with butter until lightly browned.
Toast bread in toaster.
Fry fries until golden brown.
Heat cheese sauce on top of stove.
Combine ingredients in this order on each plate:
bread, turkey, cheese sauce, fries, paprika.
Enjoy!

title: scalloped corn
directions: In crock-pot, empty corn, milk and slightly beaten eggs.
Roll crackers into fine crumbs.
Add to other ingredients and stir well.
Cook on high heat one hour, stirring every 15 minutes or until thick.

title: patty sue's candy coated popcorn
directions: Note: This will not work in microwave!

title: cocktail cheese ball
directions: Put all cheeses together; let stand until room temperature. Beat until real creamy.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion; beat until well blended.
Put in refrigerator until set and able to handle.
Shape into ball.
Roll it in crushed pecans or walnuts. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: jeff's special dip
directions: Mix drained tuna, cream cheese and mayonnaise to a creamy but fairly thick consistency.
Add onion and 3 tablespoons horseradish sauce.
Mix and add salt and pepper to taste; chill. Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: sweet and saucy meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, garlic salt and parsley.
Shape into small balls and brown in skillet with shortening.
Pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over meatballs. Cover and let simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Add salt and pepper (a little of both). Pour in casserole dish.
Slice 1/2 stick margarine over top.
Just before baking, cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggs diane
directions: Bake in 8 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until not runny and light brown on top.

title: kahlua pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in Kahlua, corn syrup, evaporated milk and pecans. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° until firm, about 40 minutes. Chill.

title: cherry delight
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into containers or casserole dish and keep in freezer.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients until shortening melts.
Mix lukewarm water, yeast and teaspoon of sugar; set aside until first mixture cools.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs.
Add both mixtures and 8 cups flour; mix well.
Pour melted butter over top and refrigerate.
This will keep several days.

title: old fashion candied yams
directions: Peel
and cut yams in quarters.
Place in medium sauce pan. sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Add water, butter, salt and vanilla.
Cook and simmer over medium heat until liquid forms a syrup.

title: quick garden cheese soup
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon cubes, pepper, vegetables and hash browns. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover for 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and the soup is hot.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large bowl; mix oil, cake mix and eggs.
Stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in candy bits from cake mix.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
With bottom of glass dipped in flour, flatten to 1/4 inch thickness.
Bake at 375 degrees for 6-8 minutes or until edges are light golden brown. Cool for 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Spread frosting over warm cookies.
Immediately sprinkle each with candy bits from frosting.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating with electric mixer.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each one.
Stir in mashed pumpkin and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and spice and add to cream mixture, stirring just until moistened, then stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: apple bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare apple slices with apple peeler/corer/slicer.
Cut slices in half.
Unroll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half to make 16 triangle strips. Place 3 to 4 apples at the wide end of each strip and roll up. Arrange bundles in pan or clay baker.
Zest one teaspoon orange rind; set aside.
Juice orange; pour into pan or baker but not over bundles.
Drizzle bundles with butter.
Mix zest, sugar and cinnamon; spoon over bundles.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: potato slices baked with onion butter
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine
butter,
onion soup mix and salt.
Pour water into
a
quart casserole dish.
Scrub potatoes and cut into
1/4-inch slices (do not peel).
Arrange a layer of slices in
casserole;
spread
with a tablespoon of onion mixture.
Repeat, making
layers.
Cover
and bake 45 minutes to an hour or until potatoes fork-tender.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef, green pepper and onion; pour off fat.
Blend in pizza sauce, mushrooms, garlic salt and oregano.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
In a small bowl, mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour over sauce mix and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: yeast biscuits to freeze
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside.

title: vegetarian lasagne
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add carrots and mushrooms. Cook until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, olives and oregano.

title: plantation chowder(our favorite winter soup)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 3 1/2 cups boiling water; pour mixture over dried corn in a large saucepan.
Let stand to reconstitute 2 hours.
Pour additional boiling water over onions and cover.
Let stand to reconstitute 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add flour.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bubble coffeecake
directions: Shape pieces of dough into 1 1/2-inch balls (about the size of walnuts).
Mix sugars and spices in a bowl.
Dip balls into butter and roll in sugar/spice mixture.
Place 1 layer of balls in a well-greased 10-inch tube pan, sides slightly touching.
Sprinkle with some of the nuts.
Top with another layer of balls, placing them in the wells created by the first layer.
Sprinkle with more nuts.
Continue until pan is near two-thirds full.
Allow space for it to rise again.
Allow to rise about 35 minutes.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Boil together the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add the soda. Stir well.
Pour over the popcorn with the peanuts added.
Put in pan and bake 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and stir in broth and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Warm
cup milk.
Dissolve the sugar and shortening in the
milk; add yeast.
(If using dry yeast, substitute 1/2 cup water for the milk when dissolving the yeast.) Add 2 cups of flour to the yeast mixture; let stand for 45 minutes.
Add remainder
of milk and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Mix and refrigerate.
Roll
out
dough
and
let
rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Make
into
rolls
and
bake in a moderate (350°) oven until nicely browned.
The dough will keep in the refrigerator for about a week.

title: china town chicken with zucchini
directions: Cook rice as directed, then mix in green onions.
While rice is cooking, saute chicken and garlic in oil until chicken is white.
Add soy sauce and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring some. Add zucchini and water chestnuts.
Cook until zucchini is crisp-tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Add water-cornstarch mix and stir until thick and clear.
Serve over rice-onion mixture.

title: barbecue sauce(for pork, ribs or chicken)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer about 45 minutes or longer. Brush on prepared ribs.
Broil about 10 minutes on each side.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; continue beating until stiff.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop cookies by teaspoon onto ungreased foil.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.

title: ranch style dressing
directions: Blend everything together in a blender.
Taste best after 1 day so flavors may blend.

title: four layer cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine and heat until smooth the pudding mix, milk and softened cream cheese.
Spread this mixture over cooled cake. Drain crushed pineapple and place over cream filling.
Place whipped topping over top and sprinkle with chopped pecans. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: apricot pecan chicken
directions: Line small baking dish with foil.
Place chicken, skin side up (may also use skinless chicken).
Spread jar or apricot preserves over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste every 20 minutes. Sprinkle with pecans before serving.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges (save juice).
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat mixture.
Add jello and dissolve.
Mix in 1 pint orange sherbet.
Add mandarin oranges.
Chill.

title: natural pick-me-up elixir
directions: Mix together and drink one in the morning and one at night.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Layer bread cubes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and salt mixture.
Add optional raisins, cinnamon or vanilla in 8 x 8 pyrex or microwave dish.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Soften oleo; cream with sugar and flour.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top after you put into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Strain berries.
Sweeten to taste.
Save a few for garnishing. Add lemon ice and ginger ale and serve.
If you use frozen berries, do not strain or sweeten.

title: valley coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper and onion in a large bowl. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan and pour over slaw while still hot.
Toss and refrigerate for several hours or overnight for full flavor.

title: apple-oat crumb
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place apple slices in an 8-inch square baking pan, and sprinkle with orange rind and juice.

title: monster cookie
directions: Beat eggs; cream with margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop for giant cookie.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°. For smaller cookie, drop by teaspoon and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: *Cook for a short time in microwave with water and a pinch of sugar.

title: porcupines in tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients and shape into 2-inch balls. In a large skillet, cook meat until balls are brown on all sides; drain on paper towels to remove excess fats. Place in a deep baking dish, 9 x 13 x 2-inch. Prepare Tomato Sauce.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix and let set out overnight to sour.
Refrigerate for 5 days.
Feed to make bread.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Put in airtight bag or bowl.
Before serving, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: cornflake chip cookies
directions: Melt oleo and shortening; cream with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder.
Stir in oats, cornflakes, coconut, raisins, chocolate chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen 2 or 3-inch cookies.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, oil and salt over low burner until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over drained vegetables.
Let stand overnight. The amount of onions and celery is your preference.
This salad keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in water until tender.
Add both cans of soup and cheese.
Heat until desired temperature and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and simmer. Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain.
Chop 1 cup Cheddar cheese and add to shells.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter both sides of bread and place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or glass casserole dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spoon sausage over bread and sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat jello and pineapple until jello dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Add buttermilk and other ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and onion and steam until tender.
Drain excess water.
Mix squash, soup, sour cream and almonds.
Spread evenly into casserole dish.
Sprinkle dressing mix over top and bake in oven at 350° until topping is brown.

title: creamed turkey in pastry shell
directions: In medium saucepan melt 2 Tbsp. of margarine.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat about 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove mushrooms, leaving juices in pan.
Stir in cornstarch.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add remaining margarine, salt, pepper and onion salt.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in turkey and mushrooms until well mixed. Serve in puff pastry shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together well sugar, Crisco, eggs, cocoa, baking powder, salt, vanilla and syrup and add flour.
Mix well and bake in loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in margarine.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Heat.
Add sour cream.
Layer crushed Doritos, chicken, sauce and cheese alternately, 2 layers each.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: citrus sunshine punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl. Stir until blended. Serve immediately.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: zinger cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Cut Zingers in half and place in 9 x 13-inch pan, filling side up.

title: cabbage bean soup
directions: Salt and pepper ground chuck and brown in soup pot.
Drain meat well.
Cut cabbage into small strips and combine with meat and tomatoes.
Add enough water to cover ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Accent, sugar and chili powder.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: vanilla butter frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and oleo; stir in vanilla and milk.
Beat until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water together and cook until thick. Add Jell-O and cool. Line baked pie crust/shell with raw fresh strawberries.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries. When ready to serve, cover with Cool Whip.

title: texas hash
directions: Fry green peppers and onions in a small amount of oil until peppers start to change color.
Crumble hamburger over peppers and cook until done.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Bring to boil butter, cocoa and cola.
Add to flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown until partially cooked (light brown).
Place in casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce and spice mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take from oven and spread with Mozzarella.

title: hot shrimp salad casserole
directions: Combine shrimp, celery, water chestnuts, eggs and onion. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper; stir into shrimp mixture.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese omelette
directions: Beat eggs, milk, onion and seasoned salt.
Tear ham into small pieces; add egg mixture.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sailburg steaks
directions: Mix ingredients (except mushroom soup) together and form into patties.
Brown and drain grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup; simmer for 1/2 hour on each side.
Serve over rice or noodles. Yields 4 servings.

title: amish rhubarb bread
directions: In a bowl, blend all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
In a small bowl, mix together 1/2 cup sugar (either white or brown) and 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Sprinkle the mixture over unbaked bread. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 5 layer dinner
directions: Layer in casserole in the order given.
Salt and pepper each layer. More tomatoes may be added, if needed.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Chill.

title: supper pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, about 1 tablespoon garlic and onion; cook until done.
Cook instant mashed potatoes (usually the serving for 8 is enough).
Place ground meat at the bottom of a casserole.
Be sure it is tall enough to layer. Layer the mushroom soup (do not add milk) on top of ground beef. Next, layer green beans.
On top, layer mashed potatoes.
Cover and bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Blend meat, tomato sauce, beaten eggs, bread crumbs and A.1.
sauce thoroughly.
Fold in diced Velveeta cheese and shape into loaf. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: maine baked beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Need large bowl as beans will swell.
Next morning, place drained beans in crock-pot.
Bury onion and score salt pork (make gashes in it).
In beans, add salt, pepper, dry mustard and molasses.
(Be careful not to add too much molasses, as will make beans hard.)
Cover with boiling water and cook on high in crock-pot all day.

title: hummingbird cakeroswell, new mexico
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add remaining and stir until well mixed.
Do not beat.

title: chick's appetizer
directions: Open and spread out uncooked rolls to cover a jelly roll pan. Bake it for about 10 minutes at 400°.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion and spread on cooled base.
Cover with chopped vegetables and press down on cheese mixture.
Cut into squares about 1 1/2-inches wide and enjoy!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Mix until smooth and add one 8 ounce container Cool Whip. Freeze, covered, for 5 to 6 hours.
Can be drizzle with chocolate before serving.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring coffee, sugar and water to a boil.
Boil slowly for 10 minutes.
Cool and add vodka.
Place mixture in two one-quart bottles and add 1/2 vanilla bean to each bottle.
Seal bottles (tape will do) and store in a cool, dark place for two to four weeks.
Gently agitate daily.

title: hamburger bean bake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook beef and onion; drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, beans and soup.
Heat to boiling.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix Bisquick with water.
Roll and lay like lattice on top of mixture.
Bake until Bisquick is brown.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash in round portions.
Add onions, green peppers, red peppers and garlic. Sprinkle with salt. Cover with 2 trays of ice and let set 3 hours.
Drain real good.
On stove, heat the vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Add drained squash. Boil about 10 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.

title: rice pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, salt and flour. Mix well. Gradually add milk. Mix well. Place over rapidly boiling water, stirring until mixture coats spoon. Pour a little of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, beating constantly. Add egg yolks to hot mixture in double boiler. Stir in rice and raisins; cook 2 minutes. Add vanilla. Put into baking dish.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Blend in one can tomato soup. Sift together all dry ingredients and add with raisins and nuts. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, or until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain off all grease.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
This can be baked or made in the electric skillet or on top of the stove.
Add tomato juice as needed to make casserole creamy.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine well, but do not beat.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Instead of doing drop cookies, I put it all in my cookie pan with sides on it and cook it all in pan and cut a bar.
Mix all ingredients well and pour in pan.
Bake at 350°.
Keep watching to be sure it does not overcook.
Let it cool for a while before you try to cut them out.
Glaze with 10x sugar, mixed with lemon or orange juice.

title: olive balls
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter in food processor.
Blend in flour, cayenne pepper and paprika.
Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive, covering completely.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 20 minutes or until browned on top at 350°.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Place broth and rice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cool. Stir together with remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with additional olive slices.

title: winter gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Whip the cream and fold into the mixture.
Tear into pieces the cake and put 1/2 of it in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Put 1/2 of the mixture over the cake pieces.
Put 3 large Butterfingers in food processor and break up.
Sprinkle the candy on the cake and filling.
Repeat the layering process, using another 3 candy bars.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts if you desire.
Best when made the day before. Enjoy!

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Put egg yolks with 1/3 of the butter in the top of a double boiler. Keep water in bottom of pot hot, but not boiling. Stir the mixture constantly. When butter melts, add another portion and as it melts and the mixture begins to thicken, add the rest of the butter, stirring all the time. As soon as the mixture is thick, remove from heat and add seasonings. This sauce is delicious served over vegetables.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate or freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bean dip
directions: Melt cheese; stir in bean-bacon soup, sour cream and onions. Cover and store in refrigerator.
If you like hot dip, add 2 jalapeno peppers, chopped finely.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie shell, bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Then turn temperature down to 325° for 45 minutes, until top is brown.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking dish.
Slice onion over the top.
Mash up tomatoes and add salt and pepper.
Pour over the top of chops and onions.
Cover dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serve over rice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together the flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in square pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Ice with favorite icing when cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water. Add the ice cubes, cranberry sauce, bananas, apples and nuts.
Mix and chill. Delicious and easy!

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients.
Quickly fold together until flour is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cheesy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into small balls (1-inch).
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish to keep warm.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir in garlic and mushrooms.
Saute a few minutes.
Turn heat down to low; stir in whipping cream, Parmesan cheese and 1/2 of tomato sauce.
Simmer a few minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour over half of noodles, then add rest of noodles while stirring.
(Do not soak up all of juice with noodles; it will get dry later.)

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make tea; use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and pour into a greased 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Mix together the next two ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Do not mix these two layers together.
Pour 1 1/2 cup hot water over all this in pan.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or by itself.

title: two-minute microwave fudge
directions: In microwave pan, sift together sugar and cocoa.
Pour in milk as to puddle.
Lay on this the oleo.
Do not stir! Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Take out, beat and add nuts.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Flatten and spread with a dollop of mushroom soup.
Roll up with 1/3 slices of bacon on outside.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 325°° until bacon is done.
Yields 120.

title: mini pizza snacks
directions: Arrange muffins on paper plates.
Spread with spaghetti sauce. Top with cheese and sprinkle with oregano.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Can put topping on this if preferred.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8 inch square baking pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Beat eggs, pulp and liquid. Mix other ingredients. Add nuts and raisins. Beat well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
When beaten together, add eggs, one at a time and vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Line bottom with wax paper and flour.
Put in cold oven. Cook at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta bolognese
directions: In a skillet saute ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil until meat loses its pinkness then transfer to a pan.
Peel and chop onion then dice celery and carrot.
Chop ham into small pieces and saute in remaining oil with onion, celery and carrot.
Transfer to pan with ground meat and combine all.
Add water, tomatoes or tomato puree, garlic, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes, then add the wine or chicken broth and cook for a few more minutes.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 frying pans cook bacon and ground beef separately.
When the hamburger is cooked put in the onion. When the bacon is done cooking put in the green pepper.
Put it on low heat.
Put the cooked rice in a large mixing bowl, mix the hamburger, bacon, onion and green pepper.
Mix in the tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and put in a 13 x 9 inch casserole pan.
Make sure to spray cooking spray in casserole pan.
Top with shredded cheddar cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until cheese is golden brown.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except nuts, with blender.
Add nuts (may
need	to
use
hands).
Mold	into round shapes and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: easy classic lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna noodles as package directs.
In bowl, combine Ricotta, Parmesan cheese and eggs; mix well.
On bottom of a 15 x 9-inch greased baking dish, spread 1/2 cup pasta sauce.
Top with half each of the lasagna noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, sausage, pasta sauce and Mozzarella. Repeat layers.
Top with parsley.
Cover; bake 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover; let stand for 15 minutes before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, except jalapenos, and simmer until excess liquid is reduced.
Add jalapenos and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, the longer you simmer the hotter the salsa.
Serve chilled.
Pass the chips.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Combine onions, garlic, bay leaf, red pepper, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and beans in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot rice.
Serve with hot pepper sauce, if desired.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add onion.
Place beef and onions in a 9-inch baking dish.
Add layer of Tater Tots, covering beef. Spread soup over evenly and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into pieces.
Trim fat.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly brown in pan.
Chop onion and then saute them.
Add tomato soup plus a can of water and stir.
Add meat. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Stir once in awhile.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix and simmer burger, garlic salt, basil, salt, stewed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and salt.
Layer in a greased pan.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture, shredded cheeses and meat sauce in 3 layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced carrots(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cook carrots 5 minutes; drain.
Cut in strips or lengths or whatever size you want, I guess.
I just left the baby carrots as they were.
Combine other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes. Strain liquid over carrots.
Refrigerate 8 hours or more.
Drain well and serve.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve as dip.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add soda to flour.
Add to butter mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.

title: quick broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed, except cut cooking time in half. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If dry, add a little milk.

title: extra special stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs; cover with cold water and let cool.
Crack, peel and halve eggs.
Mix yolks and other ingredients.
Fill egg halves.
Garnish with paprika.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger meat, flakes, eggs, salt, pepper, soy sauce, garlic powder, catsup and onion all together well.
Make in 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; drain fat.

title: oh-so creamy fudge
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Stir until mixture is well mixed and creamy smooth (about 1 or 2 minutes).
Put into a greased pan and let set.
Enjoy!

title: corn bake
directions: Mix margarine with eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish (greased).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done (lightly brown).

title: jane's pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and cover with boiling water. Let stand 15 minutes. Drain. Add sugar, salt and vinegar. Simmer 30 minutes and can. Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: peppy pizza pasta
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
In bowl, combine all the ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: black-eyed peas salsa
directions: Place peas in a colander, rinse with cold water and drain. Combine tomatoes and next 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir in peas.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Place in a lettuce lined compote or bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: west texas tortilla soup
directions: Cook garlic in butter in large saucepan, 2 minutes.
Add cumin; cook and stir 1 minute.
Add broth, tomatoes, picante and bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in cilantro.
Place 1/4 cup of cheese in bottom of 8 soup bowls.
Ladle 1 cup soup over cheese; top with tortilla strips.
Makes 8 servings.

title: soda cracker bars
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and evaporated milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter to sugar mixture, mix well. Add coconut and crushed crackers, stir well. Cool slightly. Press mixture into a lightly buttered 8 x 8 inch glass baking dish. refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Cut into small squares.

title: southern chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken until tender in about 2 quarts water, salted to taste.
Cut Crisco into flour; add egg, then water, 1 tablespoon at a time, as needed.
Mix well.
Place on floured board and roll as for pastry shell.
Let rest, covered with kitchen towel, for about 30 minutes.
Cut in strips and drop into boiling broth with chicken.
Cook for about 12 minutes or until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Layer chicken atop.
Combine next 3 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of chicken with mushroom soup

title: lemon meltaways
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together like for pie crust until crumbly.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs and stir in next 3 ingredients until well blended.
Pour over hot crust.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes more.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cool and cut into bars.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.

title: mushroom turnovers
directions: Mix cheese and butter thoroughly.
Add flour and work in well until smooth.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large pan, cook meat until tender, 2 to 3 hours.
When cool, cut up meat in small pieces.
Add back to broth the meat, potatoes, carrots and onion and cook until tender.
Add peas, corn and tomatoes.
Cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Use salt and pepper as you like.
You can use some tomato juice if soup gets too thick.
Left over beef roast makes good soup, too.

title: orange honey
directions: In a heavy, medium saucepan on low heat, warm the jar of marmalade and cornstarch; stir constantly.
Bring to a boil about 1 minute until thickened.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: meat loaf
directions: With rolling pin, crush saltines to make fine crumbs.
Combine meat, saltine crumbs, eggs, 1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce, black pepper and garlic.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and tomato (save some for topping later).
Mix thoroughly.
Form into loaf shape and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour remaining Worcestershire sauce over meat loaf and pepper lightly.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn oven down to about 325° and bake for one to one hour and 15 minutes.
Thirty minutes before meat loaf is done, top with reserved onion, pepper and tomato.
Fifteen minutes before meat loaf is done, pour a can of tomato sauce (or Italian style tomatoes) over meat loaf.
Cook, uncovered, the last 15 minutes.
Then enjoy!

title: date cake
directions: Combine dates with water; cool to room temperature.
Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well. Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture, beating.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Slice chicken in strips no larger than 2 1/2 x 1/2-inch. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; let stand 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cornstarch and oil; turn to mix and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix in egg whites and let stand 30 minutes.
In a large skillet over medium high heat, saute chicken in butter just until opaque throughout and a little golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon and keep warm.
Add tomato, vinegar, cream and tarragon to pan.
Increase heat to high and stir until mixture is blended and consistency of heavy cream.
Put chicken back in pan with half the parsley and turn gently to mix.
Heat through.
Correct seasoning with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma benson's coffee bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup milk.
Mix remaining milk, sugar, egg, salt, butter and cardamom in a large bowl.
Add a small amount of the flour and mix well.
Add yeast and remaining flour, beating with a wooden spoon until dough is smooth and firm. Sprinkle dough with a bit of flour; cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: apricot nectar sheet cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased pan about 9 x 11-inches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hearty chili
directions: Cook and stir green pepper, onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil in Dutch oven, over medium heat, until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from Dutch oven.

title: lime torte
directions: Chill Milnot overnight in refrigerator.
Juice 2 lemons and grate 1/2 of 1 lemon.
Set the jello and water in refrigerator until "soupy."
Add sugar and coloring to lemon juice.
Add jello and whipped Milnot.
Roll crumbs and put in pan (line the bottoms and sides).
Pour jello mixture in and sprinkle some of the crumbs on top.
Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, oil and egg.
Add rhubarb and sour milk; then add flour, salt, soda and walnuts.

title: maple syrup
directions: Combine sugars and water.
Dissolve while bringing to a boil by stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; cool and add flavoring.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: pears preserve cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla, allspice and flour.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in preserves and add pecans.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
When cake is done and out of the oven, poke holes all over the top of the cake.
Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved; spoon jello mixture over cake and refrigerate until jello sets.
Then cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate until serving.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Blend shortening and oleo together in large mixing bowl on medium speed.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour and soda.
Add gradually to mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Begin and end with flour.
Add coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: garlic grits
directions: Boil water rapidly.
Add grits and salt.
Stir in margarine and cheese while grits are cooking.
Remove from stove.
Beat 2 eggs in measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Combine with grit mixture.
Put in casserole.
Top with corn flake crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with dinner or burgers.

title: chicken fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook chicken breast and cut into cubes. Cook pasta. Bring chicken broth, water, cream and butter to a boil. Stir in pasta. Cook for 5 minutes. Stir in broccoli, bell pepper and carrots. Return to a boil and continue cooking for 2 minutes. Let stand for 8 to 10 minutes for sauce to thicken. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: black bean & corn salsa
directions: Serve as dip or as a dressing over lettuce (use sparingly).

title: cherry salad
directions: Pour cherries and juice into saucepan.
Bring to a boil, add sugar and Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and chill until partially jelled.
Fold in Jell-O and nuts.

title: tasty baked salmon
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Drain and flake salmon and place in a 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sour cream all over.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be served with lemon.
Serves 4.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Add soup and meat together in a casserole dish. Top with Tater Tots. Bake according to Tater Tots directions.
Shred Cheddar cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: smokey's campfire stew
directions: Brown beef; add onion and cook until transparent.
Add corn, baked beans and barbecue sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve as a stew or as a topping for baked potatoes.
(This is best over a campfire, but does well on the stove.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in casserole.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cousin judy's cassola salad
directions: In a large saucepan, add sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over medium heat; stir until thick.
Add lemon juice and cool to room temperature.
Add mixture to acini de pepe.
Let sit an hour.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin-mince pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, spice, salt, eggs and milk; heat until smooth.
Spread mincemeat evenly over pie shell.
Ladle pumpkin mixture carefully over mincemeat.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 300° about 45 minutes, until filling is firm in center.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Add potatoes to 1 quart boiling water.
Return to boil.
Cover and cook 2 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients to potatoes and mix well.
Season.
Refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn; remove those that didn't pop.
Melt marshmallows and butter.
Add food coloring if desired.
Pour over popcorn. Shape into balls.
May wrap in plastic wrap and tie with colored ribbon for Christmas.

title: cabbage and noodle dish
directions: Peel and thinly slice onion.
You should have about 4 cups. Melt butter in a large skillet.
When it is hot, stir in onion, cabbage, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook over very low heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until onion and cabbage are softened.
Cook noodles as package directs.
Drain.
Sprinkle cabbage with a few drops vinegar to taste and toss to combine.
Add noodles to skillet and continue to cook until blended and all is heated through.
Serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic. Pour off grease. Add tomato paste and tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cook noodles as directed on package. Alternate layer of meat sauce, noodles and
cheese, in baking dish; beginning and ending with meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cheese knots
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coarsely crush Rice Krispies.
Melt margarine in small pan.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies and cheese.
Separate biscuits and cut each in half. Press each half in butter, cheese and cereal mixture.
With hands roll biscuit pieces into 8-inch stick.
Gently tie to form a knot.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: aunt winona's fruit salad
directions: Whip and chill cream cheese and sour cream.
After chilled, mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: If you wish you may add some fine chopped green onion and green pepper.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with cubed bread.
Fry the sausage; drain.
Sprinkle over the bread.
Layer the cheese and mushrooms (green peppers, onions).
Combine seasonings and milk with slightly beaten eggs.
Pour over bread and sausage, cheese mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 40 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Put 2 quarts salted water on to boil spaghetti.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and slice mushrooms.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix pancake syrup and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil.
Set in oven at 350°.
Let chicken cook really good. When cooked, remove sauce and foil.
Let chicken dry under broiler. Cooking time is about 1 1/2 hours.
Chicken is very tasty.
Enjoy!

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon in casserole dish.
You can sprinkle bread crumbs on top, if desired.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and butter together.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm water mixture, egg and 1/2 flour.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in by hand the remaining dough to make soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir in sugar and corn syrup. Place in microwave for 4 minutes on High, then stir in peanuts and microwave for 4 minutes.
Then add butter and vanilla to mix, blending well.
Then microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Then add baking soda; stir until foamy.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in a greased 10 x 8-inch pan.
Add pineapple. Spread in a layer.
Sprinkle cake mix.
Spoon melted butter over mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat; add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt; mix well.
Process in blender until smooth.
In bowl, fold in crabmeat and pimientos; mix well. Slice bread into 1/2-inch slices and spread on crabmeat mixture. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes 20 slices.

title: real lemon cookies
directions: Remove zest from lemon and chop.
Squeeze and reserve juice. Grind oats in food processor to meal consistency.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and lemon extract; mix well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add lemon zest and juice; mix. Fold in ground oats.
Drop by tablespoons onto prepared pans.
Bake 10 minutes; rotate trays, switch shelves and bake 10 more minutes. Cool.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend 1/2 minute or until ice is crushed.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add salt, soda, flour, rhubarb and nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and butter over the top.
Bake in a greased and floured bread pan.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Wash, drain and remove stems from cranberries.
Put through food chopper.
Add sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle gelatin over orange juice and stir until dissolved over low heat.
Combine gelatin mix, celery, apples and nuts with cranberries, mixing well.
Put in a 1-quart mold and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with mayonnaise or whipped cream.

title: golden macaroons
directions: In a large bowl, combine flaked and shredded coconut until evenly mixed.
(Flaked coconut should be broken into separate flakes with only a few very small clumps present.)
In a medium mixing bowl combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add egg whites, honey and vanilla.
Whisk rapidly until smooth.
Pour sugar and egg white mixture over coconut mixture.
Stir with a wooden spoon, then use hands and continue to blend until evenly mixed.
Cover with plastic wrap; chill for 30 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Blend in mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and garlic salt. Stir in olives and onions. Cover; chill 2 to 3 hours for flavors to blend. When ready to serve, shape cheese mixture into ball. Roll in pecans to coat. Serve with crackers. Makes 12 servings.

title: shrimp gumbo(copied from new orleans recipe)
directions: Saute okra in oil for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, onions, garlic and pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add water, tomatoes and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and sprinkle in Tabasco.
Place 1/4 cup cooked rice in each of 6 soup bowls.
Fill with gumbo and serve (about 260 calories per serving).

title: spicy corn casserole
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Transfer to a glass baking dish and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Put in cold oven and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.
Great because it can be made ahead of time.

title: london broil
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Add other ingredients.
Place pierced London broil in glass dish.
Pour marinade over and cover. Marinate 24 hours, turn once.
Grill, basting with marinade while cooking.

title: pearly gate cake
directions: Blend shortenin' 'n sugah wid mixer.
Sift flour, bakin powder 'n salt 3 times.

Now alternately add flour mixture 'n watah (2 tablespoons at a time) to the sugah mixture...add 1/2 uv aig whites...keep on puttin' in flour 'n watah til all gone...now add remaining aig whites 'n extracts...mix 'n pore in three 9-inch layer pans...bake at 325° fur 25 to 30 minutes...Cool 'n frost wid divinity icin.

title: fat free chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Combine confectioners sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl; beat until well blended.
Add cinnamon, ginger and pumpkin pie filling; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Slice off top of pumpkin.
Cut out center, leaving shell.
Place cold dip in pumpkin shell.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: fr. fischer's venison stew
directions: In a bowl, coat the meat with flour.
In large pot, brown meat in oil.
Add salt, pepper, onions, celery, bay leaf, stewed tomatoes and water.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Take bay leaf out.
Add potatoes and carrots; cover and cook until all vegetables are tender, about 25 minutes.
Mix the cornstarch with 1/4 cup water; stir into stew and heat until it thickens, stirring constantly.

title: lemon lime nut salad
directions: Combine Jell-Os; add boiling water and mix.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, milk and walnuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: mile high pie
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar, lemon juice and egg whites in large bowl.
Beat for 15 minutes or until very stiff.
Fold in Cool Whip or whipping cream and vanilla.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8. If using 2 pie shells, the pie will not be as high.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and put in ice cream freezer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Arrange whole graham crackers closely in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix vanilla instant pudding and milk together.
Pour over graham crackers. Chop the bananas up into bite size pieces onto pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over the bananas.
Spoon crushed pineapple onto Cool Whip. Arrange kiwi slices, sliced strawberries or cherries and blueberries on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter and oil until onion is yellow. Add meat.
Cook until brown.

title: beef cubes in sour cream
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes; roll in flour.
Brown on all sides in a large skillet with a small amount of oil.
Combine onions, sour cream, cheese and salt with 1/2 cup water and pour over the beef.
Simmer covered for 1 3/4 hours or until beef is tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and add sugar.
Mix.
Add sour cream.
Mix.
Sift flour, adding the soda to the last cup. Alternate, adding eggs and flour until all used.
Add vanilla. Mix.
Pour half of batter into prepared tube pan.
Mix together the 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter and swirl through batter with knife.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead just until smooth.
Roll dough into large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle fruit over dough.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Slice dough into 16 slices 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan.
Pour sugar syrup over rolls.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy mexican bread
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain and season the meat the way you like it.
Mix the corn bread mix, egg, milk and corn until well blended.
Grease a small skillet.
Sprinkle with hamburger meat in skillet, then cheese.
Top with corn bread mix.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: pecan pralines
directions: This is an old-style praline, not the creamy type found in New Orleans.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and butter chicken.
Place in large covered baking dish.
Pour in water.
Cook on 300° for 1 hour.
Remove chicken after cooking.
Mix rice, soup and broth in pan.
Place chicken on top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: walnut refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Cream shortening and both sugars together until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute at high speed.
At low speed, add nuts and then dry mixture; mix until well blended.
Press and shape dough into 3 loaves, 2-inches square and 5-inches long; wrap in Saran and chill at least 4 hours.
(Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator).

title: butter roll
directions: For biscuits, measure flour, baking powder and salt into bowl. Cut in shortening thoroughly until mixture looks like meal. Stir in almost all the milk. If dough is not pliable, add just enough milk to make a soft puffy easy to roll dough. Dust a rolling pin and rolling surface with flour. Pinch off a ball of dough, larger than a golf ball but smaller than a tennis ball, and roll it thin as you would a pie crust.
Place 3 scant tablespoons of sugar in a strip across the center of the dough's circle. Place 3 pats of butter on top of the sugar; then sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, 1/4 teaspoon of nutmeg.

Fold dough gently over the butter and sugar mixture and close the ends to seal. Place rolls, seam sides down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour warm milk or water over rolls and bake at 375° until rolls are browned and sauce is thick.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix together milk, sour cream and pudding mix.
Layer bananas and creamed mixture.
Place in baked pie crust and chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Fry meat about 10 minutes and drain. In separate bowl, mix corn meal, salt, soda, eggs, and milk; add corn and mix well. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a pan; add meat, onion, pepper, and cheese; next add the remaining batter over the meat mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian stuffed bread
directions: Brown sausage in pan.
Pour off grease.
Cook spinach until dry.
Mix sausage, spinach and cheese together.
Cut bread lengthwise.
Scrape out middle, leaving crust.
Put ingredients in bread crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
(Wrap in foil before baking.)
Let bread stand in foil 15 minutes before slicing.

title: joan's pound cake
directions: Using an electric mixer, blend eggs, sugar and butter until fluffy and creamy.
Sift flour four times.
Blend in with ingredients.
Beat until creamy; gradually add the milk.
Now add your extracts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake until cake tests done (60 minutes) at 350°.

title: spa soup
directions: Cut up cabbage, celery onions, peppers and put in large pan (Dutch oven size).	Add 1 qt. water and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Heat a bowl of soup anytime you feel hungry.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix beaten eggs, butter, flour, sugar and milk.
Blend in corn.
Bake in open casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Stir a couple of times while baking.
This may be topped with bread crumbs.
Butter the casserole before baking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into store bought or homemade pie shells.
Cook until done at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave or on stove.
Saute onion and margarine, then add soup, sour cream, about 6 ounces of cheese and heat slowly until mixed.
Peel and layer potatoes in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour sauce prepared over potatoes and bake at 325° for about 30 to 45 minutes until heated through.
Put rest of cheese on top for about the last 10 minutes.
You can make 1/2 of this recipe.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Toss apples with lemon juice in a small bowl.
Arrange apples in overlapping circles in a buttered, 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle maple syrup over apples.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Chop bell pepper and celery.
Slice onion into thin rings and separate.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil together.
Mix until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables and marinate at least 12 hours in refrigerator.

title: lime and ice cream jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add melted ice cream and mix well.
Mix in pineapple and nuts.
Thic can be mixed in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water.
Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale.
Better if stored in container in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
May be frozen.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes approximately 3 gallons.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, lemon juice and pineapple well by hand and chill for 30 minutes.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts. Chill.
Pies can be frozen.

title: party rye slices
directions: Brown the sausage and hamburger separately.
Add the cheese and garlic salt.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Roll up in a long roll.
Refrigerate.
Slice and place on small 3 x 3-inch party rye slices.
Broil until brown.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion in
margarine.
Then
pour
over bread cubes.
Add chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into first mixture.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans which have been greased.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together and put in crock-pot.
Top with grated cheese or cheese slices.
Cook 4 hours on low heat or 2 hours on high heat. Let stand at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: country club muffins
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon yellow.
In another bowl mix remaining ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Fill greased small muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: carrot cake deluxe
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, salt, eggs, cinnamon, oil and carrots.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes; blend in flour, baking soda and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch (12 cup) Bundt or tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes until a toothpick inserted in cake center comes out clean.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: bruschetta
directions: Slice bread and spread with olive oil and chopped garlic. Bake until crisp then sprinkle with herbs, tomatoes and more garlic.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of milk into flour to make thickening.
Add all other ingredients, except biscuits, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour thickening over mixture.
Place biscuits over top.
Bake until brown.

title: shrimp etouffee(cajun french)
directions: Start by making a roux.
Place oil in large hot skillet (iron) or heavy pot.
Add flour to hot oil gradually and mix well.
Brown flour as dark as possible without burning.
Put in salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and stir to coat with roux for a few minutes. Add other ingredients; continue stirring for a few minutes.
Start adding water and stir as you would to make gravy.
Add water as needed and simmer for 20 minutes to desired consistency.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 people.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into a greased 8 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute leeks and onions in butter.
Add flour, then potatoes, broth and salt.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked (may be mashed a little).
Add sour cream when ready to serve.
Spinach should be added after soup is done and before sour cream is added.

title: beer bread
directions: Very simple to make.
Pour
warm beer into dry ingredients, a little at a
time, and mix well.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake at 400° for
45 to 60 minutes; check at 45 minutes. Five minutes before done, grease top of bread with butter.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn (do not add salt).
Put in a large casserole dish that has buttered bottom and sides.
In a small heavy saucepan, add oleo, brown sugar and Karo.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add soda (this causes syrup mixture to foam).
Pour over popcorn. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Pour out on wax paper.
To keep fresh, seal in a container.
Tastes like Cracker Jacks.

title: luscious layers
directions: Prepare pudding into each of four dessert glasses.
Fold whipped topping into remaining pudding.
Spoon over plain pudding in glasses.
Garnish each with additional whipped topping, if desired.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Dissolve soda into a little warm water and then into applesauce, letting it foam over the other ingredients.
Beat and add flour, fruit and nuts. Batter to hold it together.
