Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, greased, layer uncooked rice. Combine in a separate pan the mushroom soup, celery soup and milk. Heat and pour over uncooked rice.
Then place uncooked chicken pieces from 1 entire fryer or use all chicken breasts.
Sprinkle onion soup on top of uncooked chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until well done.
Depending on your oven you may not want to remove cover.
But chicken gets nice and crispy if uncovered.
Toss a salad, make coffee and dinner is served.

title: mounds cake
directions: Make the cake the day before you want to serve it, according to package directions.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Allow to cool.
Makes holes all over cake with long-tined fork or skewer.

title: mace bundt cake
directions: Cream
butter,	add
sugar
gradually.	Cream
together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.	Beating well after each addition.
After last egg, let batter rest a while, measuring and sifting together 3 times the flour and the mace. Add to batter and
blend, stir in the nuts.
Have ready a very heavily greased Bundt pan using 2 or 3 tablespoons of shortening;
spoon
batter in.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: german honey pork stir-fry
directions: Toss pork with flour to coat.
Heat oil in a large skillet on high heat.
Add pork and stir-fry about 3 minutes until browned. Remove from skillet and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add lemon juice, honey and soy sauce to pan drippings.
Simmer about 10 minutes until slightly thickened, stirring often.
Add snow peas, onions and pork.
Cook about 2 minutes more or until peas are crisp-tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve on a bed of hot, fluffy rice.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Boil chicken; cut into pieces.
mix cream cheese, soup, 1 stick margarine, and poppy seed.
Add chicken.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and banana, beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.
Store overnight before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and Crisco over hot water.
Beat in well the sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to above ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Place raisins in small bowl.
Pour enough boiling water over to cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain raisins.
Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil, pumpkin and eggs; mix just until combined.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Put in prepared pans; bake about 25 minutes.

title: big cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cake mix, eggs and oil in a bowl. Stir together until moistened.
Press mixture into pizza pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk in a mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour melted margarine over sugar mixture.
Do not stir.
Arrange peach slices evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sugar mixture over peaches.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour hot water over broccoli to bring out the green color. Drain well. Break into small pieces.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except bacon. Chill overnight. Before serving, top with cooked, crumbled bacon.

title: old-fashioned blueberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Add blueberries, tossing gently.
Set aside.
Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate; trim off excess pastry along edges.
Spoon blueberry mixture into pastry shell; dot mixture with butter.
Roll remaining pastry to 1/8-inch thickness; transfer to top of pie. Trim off excess pastry along edges.
Fold edges under and flute. Cut slits in top of crust for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool pie before serving. Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: ham and chicken roll-ups
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Put 1/3 stick of oleo in the skillet.
Put in onion and celery; saute.
Add frozen broccoli; add soup and cheese.
Add rice and mix.
Put bread crumbs or crackers on top and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter snacking cake
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Mix cake and directed and pour mixture into cooking sheet and bake until done.
While still warm, coat top with peanut butter.
Cool and then chill in refrigerator until peanut butter is firm.
Melt chocolate and pour chocolate over top of peanut butter.
Cool and chill until chocolate is hard.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix margarine,	brown
sugar and pretzels and spread in lightly buttered dish,
x
13-inch or 11 x 7-inch.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and let cool.

title: chicken chipulos
directions: Preheat oven to 350° F. Combine the soups, chicken, green chilies, onion and sour cream in a medium size bowl.
Set aside. Rip tortillas into bite size pieces and layer 1/3 onto bottom of a 9x13 baking dish.
Layer chicken mixture on top, then a layer of cheddar cheese.
Repeat two additional times, making sure to end with cheese on the top layer.
Bake in preheated oven for about one hour.
Serves 6-8.

title: almond toffee crackle
directions: Melt butter and add sugar and nuts.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes on high.
Pour into jelly roll pan (buttered).
Let cool and crack up.

title: chip beef hot dip
directions: Rinse beef.
Shred real fine.
Mix with the other items.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pasta la cinenega
directions: Saute onions, garlic, mushrooms, basil, parsley, salt and pepper in white wine over medium heat.
Blanch vegetables and set aside in large bowl.
Add tomatoes to saute.
Remove from heat, adding spice to taste.
Toss with vegetables and serve over linguine.

title: squash casserole no. 3
directions: Cook
squash until tender, mash and drain.
Melt margarine and pour
over
stuffing and mix.
(If desired, use half poultry stuffing
and
half
cornbread stuffing.) Combine all ingredients and mix well, reserving a small amount of stuffing for the
top of
casserole.
Bake
in greased baking dish for about 40 minutes at 350° or until carrots are cooked.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
If frozen, cook for 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: quick corn flake candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in heavy boiler.
Place over heat until small bubbles form around edges; do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until blended.
Stir in corn flakes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly sprayed with Pam.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dice onion and eggs into small pieces.
Cook bacon until crispy and break into small pieces.

title: broccoli oriental
directions: Cook broccoli and chestnuts in medium pan, covered, in small amount of boiling water 10 minutes.
Drain and keep warm.
In same saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in soy sauce and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over broccoli.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas.
Mix milk and soup and cheese together; add all the ingredients together, then add chopped eggs. Place in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool completely.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over cooled brownies.

title: molasses spice cookies
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients (except granulated sugar).
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts and roll in granulated sugar.
Press down with floured tumbler.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: pastrami cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cheese with Accent, Worcestershire sauce, onions and small amount of chopped pastrami. Make into a ball. Roll in remainder of the chopped pastrami.

title: cake for strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add milk, egg, vanilla and melted butter.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine margarine, vanilla and salt. Blend well.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add flour and chocolate bits.
Mix well.
Press evenly into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, then break into irregular pieces or cut in squares.

title: irish oatmeal bread
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, baking powder and salt in large bowl. Beat egg with honey and milk and beat well.
Pour into flour mixture and mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
This batter is not smooth.
Spread batter in pan (greased) in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until crusty and tests done.
Turn out to cool.
While still warm, brush top with butter.

title: easy caramel apple pie
directions: Combine candies (each piece cut into 4 pieces) and flour.
Add apples, ice cream topping and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour mixture into frozen pie crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 375° on preheated baking sheet for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not refrigerate.

title: fluffy cheesecake dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Reserve 1/3 cup. Press rest of
crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 9-inch ungreased square pan.
Prepare
frosting
mix as package directs.
Blend cream cheese and	sour
cream
in
large	mixer bowl.
Beat in frosting gradually.	Pour over crumb mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake
for
45 minutes.	Cool; refrigerate.
Serve
topped
with
pie filling.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add oil and sugar to eggs.
Then add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together and add to mixture.
Lastly, add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix & spread
top with grated swiss cheese.
Save a little bacon for top too.

title: dave's mom's potato pancakes
directions: Place potato grating on a towel and wring the towel to extract as much moisture from the potatoes as possible.
Place potatoes in a bowl and stir in eggs.
Add flour, salt and onion.
Shape into 1/4-inch thick, 3-inch diameter (small) patties.
Saute in 1/4-inch or more hot oil.
Turn and brown until crisp.
Best served hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place alternate layers of potatoes, cheese, peppers and onions in
greased
baking dish.	Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup with milk.
Pour over potatoes;
cover.
Bake
for
1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven. Remove cover and let brown slightly.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover, chill. Makes 5 cups.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepot, saute onion and garlic in margarine until translucent.
Add potatoes and carrot; saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Add stock and dill and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Remove vegetables from pot and puree in blender with cream cheese and milk.
Return pureed mixture to pot.
Stir in cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Reheat over low heat.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Melt margarine; add both sugars and vanilla to butter and blend together.
Add eggs, one at a time, to mixture, beating after each one.
Fold in flour and pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Flour and grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool.
These freeze well.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions.
Layer strawberries, pudding mix and angel food cake (crumbled up) in bowl or you can mix it all together.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: fresh garden skillet
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Fry in oil, turning over as they brown. Cook until tender.
Serves 4.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; cream butter and sugar.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake in crisp pie crust in moderate oven approximately 1 hour or until pie will not shake.
Do not cook too dry.

title: bread "popovers"
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, flour, salt and butter.
Do not beat too much.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serve piping hot with butter or jelly.
Yields 10 to 12.

title: easy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish so pieces don't overlap. Cover with mushrooms.
Combine soup with sour cream and sherry. Pour over chicken completely covering.
Dust with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: edna's cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheeses and add pepper.
Form into a ball and roll in the pecans.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add soda to the buttermilk, then add to creamed mixture alternately with the flour mixture.
Place in greased tins and bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut
each
biscuit
into
4 pieces.
In small bowl, mix together
cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Roll each piece
of biscuit in mixture and put into Bundt pan.
Bring to boil
sugar,
cinnamon,
margarine	and vanilla.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn
out	onto waxed paper.
Do not cut, but pull pieces apart.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Chop chicken into small pieces while partially frozen.
Chop onion finely.
Also chop garlic sections.
On medium heat melt butter and stir-fry chicken, onion and garlic until chicken is no longer pink.
Add salt and pepper; simmer.
Boil noodles.
Pour chicken, onions and garlic in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Also pour in all grease from chicken pan.
Add soup and sour cream, mix well.
Add noodles; mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mushroom stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Cut pockets into thick part of breasts.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside.
Saute sausage, celery and onion.
Mix well with mushrooms, bread crumbs, parsley, remaining salt and 1/3 cup broth.
Place heaping tablespoonful stuffing into each breast pocket; secure opening with toothpick.
Brush with butter and roll in bread crumbs.

title: velvet cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add unbeaten egg and extract.
Sift flour and baking powder, then gradually add to the cream mixture.
Fill cookie press half full and form cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes five dozen.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Melt margarine; add dry ingredients together and mix with egg, apples and vanilla.
Pour in deep pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandmother's cobbler for a busy day
directions: Melt butter into rectangular casserole dish.
Mix flour and milk; spoon into butter.
Do not stir.
Pour syrup off peaches into a saucepan.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: vegetable garden pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well using a fork. Pour oil (vegetable) to coat the bottom of a large, heavy skillet.
Cook pancakes on medium heat 3 or 4 minutes each side, until nicely browned.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: copper coin salad
directions: Peel carrots; slice in 1/4-inch rings.
Cook or steam until tender-crisp; drain.
Combine soup, salad oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, dill seed and pepper in saucepan; bring to a boil to dissolve.
In 1/4 cup of water, dissolve 1 envelope gelatin and stir into hot soup until melted.
In 2-quart container, combine carrots, green pepper and onion.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables; mix well and let stand overnight.

title: microwave fish fillets
directions: Place margarine in rectangular dish or 10-inch square dish. Microwave at High (100%) until melted.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except fish.
Coat both sides of fish with butter sauce.
Arrange in dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High (100%) until fish flakes easily in center with fork, 5 to 6 minutes.

title: martha's fruit topping
directions: Wash
strawberries and slice.
Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice.
Prepare
instant
pudding
and stir in bananas. Put sliced
strawberries in glaze and mix.
Mix all together. Let chill, if possible, overnight.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 10 minutes, then drain.
Heat remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Add vegetables to tomato soup.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: meal in a pot
directions: Fry bacon crisp and break into small pieces.
Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Put all ingredients into a crock-pot and slow cook for 4 to 6 hours.

title: creamed crab meat
directions: Remove spines from crab meat, then melt butter; blend in flour and seasoning.
Add milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add crab meat and heat thoroughly; serve very hot over toast.

title: chocolate yogurt melts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients until smooth; add next 2 ingredients until mixed in.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart on lightly sprayed baking sheets.
Garnish with nut halves if desired.
Bake in preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cool on wire racks.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour water over apples.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix in mixer or blender until light.
Spread over hot cake. When cool, cover and chill in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: cottage cheese and dill dip
directions: Place cottage cheese, green onion, snipped parsley, dill weed, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and garlic powder in a blender container or food processor bowl. Cover and blend or process until smooth. Chill, covered, for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: snowman's punch
directions: Combine sugar, 2 cups water, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.

title: spaghetti sauce for 25
directions: In large pot, add water, tomatoes, paste, basil, oregano and garlic powder.
Cook on medium and let boil.
In large skillet, brown beef, then add onions and peppers.
Let brown (be sure to drain grease off beef).
Add meat to sauce and let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: szechuan shrimp
directions: Combine scallions, bamboo shoots, ginger, garlic and Tabasco in small bowl.
In second bowl, combine sugar, catsup, sherry, soy sauce and sesame seed.
In a third bowl, mix cornstarch and water. Heat oil to 400°.
Add shrimp to hot oil; cook about 2 minutes. Remove to strainer.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add contents of first bowl, then second bowl, shrimp and then cornstarch with water.
Serve over rice.

title: elvis presley's homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook together meat, onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic and tomatoes for 1 1/2 hours. Add mixed vegetables for 1/2 hour. Then mix in corn, potatoes, okra, salt and pepper. Cook for 30 minutes longer. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Drain. Combine noodles and tuna, add mayonnaise, all chopped vegetables and salt. Heat on top of stove. Add cheese and stir until cheese melts. Put in casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs tossed with olive oil or with bread stuffing. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in bite size pieces.
Put jelly, chili and mustard in crock-pot and mix.
Stir hot dogs into mixture.
Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Heat tomato juice with salt, sugar and pepper. Sift dry ingredients;
add
milk.
Blend
into
a stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls
into
hot
juice. Cook, covered, for 12 minutes. Do not overcook.
Do not remove.
Cover during cooking.
Serve at once. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Line sides and bottom of pie crust with bananas.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and sugar with electric mixer until thickens.
Pour over bananas.
Sprinkle pineapple (may need to squeeze juice out with hands) over creamy layer.
Spread top of pineapple with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top of pie.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: shawn's chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Mix 1/2 can water to soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup over chicken after 20 minutes and continue to bake for next 15 minutes.
Turkey can be used in this recipe.

title: casserole corn bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onions and bell peppers.
Mix cornbread mix with beaten eggs and both cans of corn.
Then add that to the sauteed onions and bell peppers.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Whip sour cream with fork until creamy and spread on top of casserole.
Then spread the 2 cups cheese on top of sour cream.
Return to oven (lower to 350°) and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Delicious!!!!

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip each breast in milk and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine butter, garlic and lemon juice, drizzle over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin and shortening.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool and spread with glaze. Makes 4 dozen.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg, add minced onion, 1 cup cracker crumbs, salt and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old english hot spiced cider
directions: Heat cider and sugar.
Combine together all the spices and wrap in a piece of cheesecloth.
(Will be easier to remove them after simmering.)
Simmer over low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until flavored to your liking.
Serve hot.
Great for holiday parties!

title: baked raccoon
directions: Parboil coon for 30 minutes in salt water; drain and place in shallow baking dish.
Blend spices and liberally cover coon. Surround with sliced onions.
Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Place carrots and potatoes in juice and continue to bake until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and broil to brown.

title: royal cherry sauce
directions: Drain cherries, reserving liquid.
Set cherries aside. Combine sugar, cornstarch and reserved cherry liquid in a saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Add wine, lemon juice and orange rind.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens.
Stir in cherries.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve with poultry or ham.

title: baked potato soup(baked potatoes give this soup a delightful flavor)
directions: Scrub potatoes and remove any blemishes.
Bake potatoes until partially cooked, but still firm.
Dice potatoes and set aside. Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Add chicken broth and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add cream and milk; continue stirring until mixture begins to thicken.
Add potatoes, parsley, chives, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes until thickened.
Serve with green onions, cheese and bacon as garnish.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine green beans, soup, milk, half of the onions and half of the bacon bits.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, then sprinkle remaining onions and bacon bits on top.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening until crumbly.
Add vinegar and water to flour mixture and work in until ingredients are moist.
Divide dough into balls.
Roll out onto floured board and put into pie plates.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl combine fruits and set aside.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice eggs on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Combine margarine, flour, milk, mayonnaise and pepper.
Pour on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except pecans and crackers thoroughly and shape into a ball. Roll in crackers and pecans.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Serve with graham crackers.

title: *no-cook strawberry jam
directions: Wash, stem and thoroughly crush strawberries, one layer at a time.
Place in a large bowl.
Thoroughly mix sugar into fruit; let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and Certo well in a small bowl.
Stir into fruit and stir for about 3 minutes.
A few sugar crystals will remain.

title: reuben meat pie
directions: Prick the bottom and sides of pastry shell with a fork and bake at 425° for 7 minutes.
Sprinkle corned beef in baked pastry shell.
Add cheese and top with sauerkraut.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour over sauerkraut in baked pastry shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until set. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: micro broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook bacon slices for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until crisp, with microwave at High.
Allow to cool and crumble.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese until softened.
Add Eagle Brand milk and stir well.
Add lemon juice and stir well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Cover with desired fruit topping.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over 3 quarts of popped popcorn.
Make into balls.
Add food coloring to make for different holiday.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Shred dried beef into bottom of greased baking dish. Wrap chicken in bacon and place in casserole over layer of beef and sprinkle with pepper. Blend soup (undiluted) with cream and pour over chicken. Cover. Bake at 275° for 3 hours, or uncovered for 2 1/2 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot salsa dip
directions: In a microwave dish, mix salsa and cream cheese.
Heat 2 minutes on High.
Mix again with wire whip to blend.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to microwave.
Heat on High until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Very easy and delicious.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chilies, sour cream, olives, and half of cheese together. Divide mixture in half.
To one half, add the chicken.
Roll into 12 tortillas.
Place into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover with remaining mixture, cheese, and olives.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until heated.
Serve with salsa, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, and sour cream.

title: raspberry sour cream cake
directions: Do not preheat oven. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, sugar, sour cream, oil and eggs. Beat on low speed to blend, then on medium for 4 minutes. Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured 12-cup capacity Bundt cake pan. Drop raspberries on top of batter and top with remaining batter. Place in cold oven; set temperature to 325°. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on cooling rack. When cool, spoon on Raspberry Glaze.

title: english trifle
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar to strawberries and refrigerate.
Bring milk just to boiling.
Put whole eggs and egg yolks into mixing bowl and beat until light and lemon colored.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and stir. Pour about half the hot milk into eggs, beating vigorously.
Return this mixture to rest of milk in pan and cook on low heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until mixture thickens and coats the spoon.
(I add 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with just a little cold water to make the custard firmer.)
Remove from heat.
Add rum, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir to mix.
Chill.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Dip chicken into 1/4 cup buttermilk, then roll in seasoned flour (salt and pepper).
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for 15 minutes.
Blend 1 cup buttermilk and soup; pour around chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more, or until done.
Serves 6.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and vinegar.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add paste to creamed mixture.
Sift flour with salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Add soda and vanilla.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on foil covered cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven and immediately turn off the oven.
Do not open the door until morning.
No peeking!!!

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; add sherbet just before serving.

title: pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Add yeast to water.
Stir.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix, knead and shape dough.
Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gingered honey marinade
directions: Mix all together and marinate meat in it for up to 24 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll dough into small balls. Flatten out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: famous chocolate wafer roll
directions: Reserve 1 cup whipped cream and set aside.
Spread each wafer cookie with cream and arrange in stacks of 4 or 5.
Chill 5 minutes.
Lay stacks on edge to
make one long roll.
Spread remaining whipped cream on outside of roll.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, covered (you can also put it in the freezer).
Slice at an angle to get a striped effect and serve.

title: dirt
directions: Mix
cream
cheese,
margarine	and sugar.
In separate bowl mix
pudding
and milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Take
1	large bag of Oreo cookies and crush until they have the appearance of dirt.
Alternate cookies and pudding mixture
twice.
Reserve some crushed Oreo's for top. Very cute served
in flowerpot with a silk flower stuck in the middle of crushed cookies.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook the grits according to package directions. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly until cheese melts.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: white potato pie
directions: Put potatoes in bowl; add butter, sugar, flour, eggs, milk, salt and flavoring.
Mix well and pour in an unbaked pie crust. Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and continue to cook until browned.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Put carrots in 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Add water.
Bake, covered, at 325° until carrots are tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if needed.
Makes 10 servings.

title: ham and beans
directions: Crock-pot ham shanks for 24 hours on low.
Remove shanks, save and chill stock.
Remove fat from stock.
To stock in crock-pot add the remaining ingredients and cook for 24 hours on low.
Add the meat from the shank bones.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla; mix well. Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Place heaping tablespoonful of batter in ungreased muffin cups.
Work dough 1/3 way up sides of each cup.
Fill with tablespoonful of cherry pie filling.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping.
(Makes 24 tarts.)

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan and set aside. In small bowl of electric mixer, beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/4 cup of sugar to egg whites and beat until sugar is well combined.
Set aside.	In a separate bowl, cream butter, salt, and vanilla.	Add remaining 3/4 cup sugar and egg yolks. Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk to butter and sugar mixture. Fold in reserved egg white mixture and blueberries.
Pour batter into prepared baking pan and sprinkle the top with granulated sugar. Bake for 50 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift and blend together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; stir in shortening mixture.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: pecan sandwich meat
directions: Mix dry
ingredients.
Add
water and soy sauce.
Place in sprayed can
and
cover.
Place in crock-pot with 1 inch of water. Steam on high 4 hours.

title: italian bow knots
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, kneading together with hands until smooth.
Divide into 3 portions.
Roll each portion out separately (about as thin as pastry).
Cut with pastry cutter or pizza wheel.
Tie into bows and drop carefully into hot oil; fry to light brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Dip in boiling honey or powder with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter for ten minutes.
Add next five ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well, then mix in mashed bananas.
Add all dry ingredients. Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam.
Pour batter evenly into 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Done when inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: pancakes(yields 12 servings)
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Grease griddle or pan.
Heat on medium.
Cook pancakes until dry around edges.
Turn and cook.

title: easy chicken teriyaki
directions: Stir all the ingredients, except the chicken, together in a baking dish or pan.
Add the chicken pieces and turn a few times to coat well with the sauce.
With the flesh side facing down in the sauce, cover and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ranchy potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into squares.
Boil until tender.
Drain. Combine potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix with dressing.
Top with bacon and cheese.
Serve while hot.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl and make well in center.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake 65 to 75 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes and turn out of pan.
Dust with powdered sugar or serve with whipped topping or frost.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: roulade
directions: Pound meat between wax paper into 6 x 8-inch rectangles.

With short side toward you, lay one pickle spear and spread 1 heaping teaspoon of onion and a piece of bacon about 1-inch from the end. Carefully roll steak around the filling, folding edges toward the center.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around bundle.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: rosamarina dessert(ambrosia)
directions: Cook rosamarina pasta to al dente, rinse and cool.
In saucepan, mix together eggs, drained liquid from fruit cocktail, flour and sugar.
Cook slowly, constantly stirring, until puddinglike.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.
The next day, when all ingredients are cold, mix rosamarina pasta, reserved fruit cocktail, pudding mixture and drained mandarin oranges together. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving time.
This makes a large quantity and is good for parties.

title: rack of lamb de simone
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.
Place lamb fat side down in bottom of shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven.
Place fat side up in roasting pan.
Combine mustard and rosemary; brush on lamb. Cover lamb with bread crumb mixture.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat or bone.
Reduce heat to 300°. Bake until lamb thermometer registers 140° for rare, 160° for medium or 170° for well done.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a boil; take off heat and add peanut butter.
Mix until it dissolves.
Add corn flakes.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: almost lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
In skillet, cook ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine all cheeses except Cheddar.
Place 1/2 of noodles in bottom of 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 of meat sauce and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: soy wings
directions: Mix sugar, soy sauce and seasonings in a large bowl.
Place wings in a large baking dish and pour sauce mixture over them. Bake at 350° to 375°, covered, for about 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for another 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni until tender.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Make cream base with butter, flour and 2 quarts of cream or half and half.
Saute vegetables and garlic in butter.
Add to cream base.
Add seafood to cream base.
Add parsley and seasoning to taste.
Simmer, but do not boil.
Add cream or half and half to thin.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Combine until
crumbly.
Pat mixture into bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.	Cool.

title: easy and quick meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Put into loaf pan. Pour 8 ounce can Hunt's tomato sauce over top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: corn and ham chowder
directions: Saute celery, onion and ham in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Simmer 20 minutes before serving.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, enchilada sauce or salsa, green chili peppers, chili powder and salt into meat mixture.
Cook until bubbly.
Spoon 1/3 of meat mixture into bottom of 2 quart rectangular baking dish.
Place 5 tortillas on top.
Spoon 1/2 of remaining meat mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over meat.
Repeat with remaining tortillas, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot all through.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in mayonnaise (okay to add Ranch dressing also) about 8 minutes.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: instant brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Heat and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add cream cheese, pineapple and juice and salad dressing.
Add prepared Dream Whip.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: birthday cake icing
directions: Beat margarine and shortening.
Slowly beat in confectioners sugar.
Gradually add milk and vanilla flavoring along with confectioners sugar.
Cover with damp towel until used.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Soften at room temperature to use.

title: ming chicken crepe
directions: Stir-fry sprouts, mushrooms and pea pods in a wok or skillet in 1 or 2 tablespoons of oil for about 2 minutes until done. Set aside. Stir-fry chicken in oil. When nearly done, add vegetables. Toss; remove to serving platter and sprinkle with uncooked green onions.

title: candy bar pie
directions: In pan melt coffee in water.
Add broken chocolate bar pieces and stir over low heat until melted.
Cool slightly and fold into Cool Whip.
Fill pie crust and freeze 10 minutes before serving. Remove from freezer and serve.

title: fried rice
directions: First cook eggs in hot frying pan sprayed with Pam.
Turn over and cook slightly until done.
Put on plate and chop into little pieces; set aside.
Heat about 2 tablespoons oil in wok or frying pan and cook each vegetable separately until brown and hot.
Take out of wok and set aside.
Add about 1 or 2 tablespoons of oil in wok and brown desired choice of meat.
Add cooked vegetables, eggs and white rice to browned meat.
Add desired amount of salt and pepper and mix thoroughly; may have to add about 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil to rice mixture.
Mix together well.
Add desired amount of soy sauce; mix well and serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix sour cream, corn, eggs and oil.
Add corn meal, baking powder and salt and stir in 1 cup of the cheese.
Add onion and chilies.
Mix well and put into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork n bean cake
directions: Put the raisins in the boiling water; set aside.
Beat the eggs, oil, brown sugar, white sugar and pork and beans.
Add the raisins and water and the vanilla. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken rustica
directions: In frying pan, melt butter.
Add chicken.
Cook.
Add water, milk and soup.
Stir to blend.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: nip it in the bud spuds
directions: In a large bowl, mash potatoes until smooth.
Add the cream cheese in small pieces and the butter.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Stir in sour cream.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and pat dry chicken.
Rub each breast with butter.
In a Ziploc bag, combine cornflakes and basil.
Coat each chicken breast in cornflake mixture and place in casserole dish.
Dot each chicken breast with a pat of butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: juicy cooler
directions: Combine the juices and sugar in a pitcher. Stir until sugar dissolves. Add chilled sparkling water; stir. Serve over crushed ice.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large enameled canner or stainless steel.
Cook until thick as you like, stirring to prevent burning or scorching.
Seal in hot jars.
Process in hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 to 8 quarts.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together and put into 12 muffin cups, Use paper liners. Drizzle with 2 Tbsp Hershey's syrup.
Freeze.
They taste surprisingly like a peanut butter cup.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil margarine, milk, and sugar for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add oats, cocoa, vanilla. Mix well. If mixture seems to soup add more oats. Drop mixture by the spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: super meat balls
directions: Put all ingredients, except meat, into a blender and blend until smooth.
Mix into meat and shape into balls.

title: london chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Brown mushrooms.
Place chicken in large casserole.
Mix soups (undiluted); pour over chicken.
Place mushrooms on top.
Refrigerate.
When ready to bake, add wine. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream cheeses together and form into a ball.
Add Worcestershire, dried beef and green onions.
Mix all together to form a ball.
Put ball on a plate and serve.
For a 1/2 recipe, subtract 1/2.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix other ingredients and add to broccoli.
Place in 3 quart casserole and top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, butter and cinnamon in a medium bowl; mix well.
Press into a 10-inch spring-form pan; set aside.

title: candied almonds
directions: Beat egg white at high speed with an electric mixer until foamy. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating 2 to 4 minutes or until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves. Fold in almonds. Melt butter in a 9-inch square pan or larger in a 325° oven. Add almonds to pan and bake, stirring every 5 minutes, 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Watch carefully! Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, one box of pudding mix, cream cheese, club soda and eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer at high speed for two minutes.
Take out 1 cup of the batter and set aside.
Pour remaining batter into a greased angel food or Bundt pan.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix 2/3 apple cider to 1/3 cranberry juice in crock-pot.
Add 2 to 3 allspice berries, 5 to 6 whole cloves and 1 to 2 cinnamon sticks.
(Can put cinnamon sticks in a whole orange, if desired.)

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: In heavy gauge saucepan combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to full rolling boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add mint chocolate morsels; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla extract.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: old-fashioned butter roll
directions: Mix flour, shortening, water and 1 cup of milk.
Roll out like pie crust.
Mix butter, 1 cup of sugar, vanilla and lemon.
Put butter mixture on crust; roll up like a jelly roll.
Cook remainder of milk and sugar over low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour over rolls.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: peachy nut cake
directions: Place peaches in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly on peaches. Pour melted butter over mix. Add nuts. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: orange slice christmas cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of the flour with nuts and fruit.
Cream oleo and sugar, beat in eggs one at a time.
Mix soda, salt, and flour; add to creamed mixture with milk, add fruit and nuts.
Bake in 250° oven, in well greased, large loaf pan, or two smaller ones, for 2 1/2 hours.
Turn out immediately and glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar and small can frozen orange juice.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough overnight.
Cut up one of the loaves in small pieces and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over the bread in the pan.
Cut up the second loaf and place over that.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
To reheat, warm in 350° oven for 10 minutes wrapped in aluminum foil.

title: meatless taco salad
directions: In large skillet, add tofu and taco seasoning mix.
Add the same amount of liquid as on the seasoning package directions.

title: aunt emily's rhubarb pie
directions: Line a pie pan with pie crust, then put in rhubarb.
Mix all together sugar, flour, butter, egg and boiling water.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: best all-american brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften butter. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Add butter.
Beat in flour mixture.
Spread batter into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage and egg bake
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl; beat until smooth.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.
May place crescent roll dough in baking pan and on top of casserole and omit bread if preferred.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: flank steak(rice as a side dish)
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Combine remaining ingredients as marinade.
Marinate 4 hours or overnight.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes each side (for medium-rare), brushing with marinade.
Slice thinly across grain.
(May serve as main course and/or appetizer at room temperature with rye bread.)

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon grease.
Pour off excess grease.
Add tomatoes and all other ingredients, except bacon and beans. Cook, stirring, until veggies are soft. Add drained beans and bacon.
Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend on high.
Cook like pancakes.

title: blarney stones
directions: Bake cake according to box instructions in sheet cake pan. Cool completely. Cut into 2 inch squares. Mix sugar, half and half and butter in saucepan. Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes; pour over powdered sugar. Thin with half and half; icing should be very thin. Ice top and sides of each square and roll in peanuts.

title: sweet potato casserole with topping
directions: Mix and pour into casserole.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Fry or boil the chicken breasts until done.
Chop or shred chicken.
Scoop 1/4 cup chicken and about 1/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese onto a large flour tortilla.
Fold up bottom over filling, then fold in sides and roll up.
Secure with toothpick, if necessary.
Heat oil in electric frypan or deep fat fryer.
Cook each chimi until all sides are nicely browned.

title: baked sliced apple slices
directions: Pare, core and slice apples into eighths.
Combine brown sugar, bread crumbs, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend.
Spread 1 tablespoon butter on entire insides of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Fill pan with alternate layers of apples, brown sugar mixture and orange juice, ending with sugar mixture on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 15 minutes. Uncover; continue to bake about 1/2 hour longer, or until apples are soft.
Serve warm or cold with cream or ice cream.

title: cornish hens with chestnut-sausage stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook onion and celery in Italian dressing, stirring until tender.
Add sausage and cook 5 minutes or until browned.
Stir in bread crumbs, chestnuts, pine nuts and herbs.
Stuff hens with mixture.
Close cavities with skewers and tie legs together with string.
Place in roast pan on racks.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil and roast 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue roasting 15 minutes, approximately until done.

title: fruited chef's salad
directions: Arrange quartered hard-cooked eggs, slivered ham or turkey and canned pineapple chunks on crisp lettuce.
Sprinkle with a little crisp bacon.
Serve with a favorite dressing.

title: shrimp creole with rice
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in the oil or shortening.
Combine next 8 ingredients.
Add to first ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add shrimp an continue cooking until mixture is heated through.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Serve hot shrimp creole over rice.
Makes 50 servings.

title: curried chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add chicken, apples, celery, tomatoes and onions.
In a small bowl, combine picante sauce, mayonnaise, chutney and curry powder, mixing well.
Combine with pasta mixture; cover and chill.
Serves 6.

title: easy turkey lasagne
directions: Brown turkey and onion together slowly.
Pour off excess fat. Add spaghetti sauce, garlic and oregano.
Cook on simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread with half the Ricotta; add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° about 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely. Combine cream cheese, sugar, 2 cups Cool Whip and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Spread on crust. Combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat with mixer 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 8 hours and serve.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well; shape into a ball.
Chill until firm.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: creamed cucumbers and onions
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in a bowl.
Combine the mayonnaise, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Mix well and add to cucumbers and onions.
Can be served immediately or refrigerated.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat the oven at 350°.

In a large bowl, combine 1/4 cup of the reserved pineapple juice (discard remaining juice or set aside for another use), the pineapple, orange juice, grated orange peel, milk, eggs, brown sugar, oil and poppy seed.

title: wine baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts, breast bone side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange mushrooms around chicken.
Pour wine over chicken and sprinkle with parsley, whole tarragon, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Yields 8 servings with 154 calories per serving.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Add tablespoon olive oil.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix ingredients except cheese and potatoes. Spread in deep pie dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese, mashed potatoes and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: lindy's chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken until meat comes off bones.
Take bones out.
Put in potatoes, carrots, onions, mushrooms and celery; cook until tender.
Add green pepper, green beans and peas; cook 5 minutes. Add cabbage and cook until cabbage is done.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together; can be served immediately or refrigerated.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put
sugar,
milk,
butter,
cocoa
and salt in a large saucepan and
bring
to
a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the rolled
oats,
vanilla, nuts and coconut.	Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper to make cookies.

title: fried liver with bacon and onion
directions: In a large frying pan, brown bacon and onion.
Dip liver into egg mixture.
Coat liver with bread crumbs.
Add liver to bacon and onion mixture.
Continue frying until well browned.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve chilled with salad crackers or on a leaf of lettuce. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pint size pot roast(4 servings)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat.
Reserve leftover flour.
Brown meat in cooking oil in Dutch oven.
Pour off drippings.
Add water, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Turn and add more water if necessary while cooking.
Add onion and continue cooking, covered, for 30 minutes or until meat is tender and onion is done.
Remove meat and onion to platter and keep
warm.
Combine reserved flour and 1/4 cup water.
Add to cooking liquid and cook, stirring constantly, for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Place layers in casserole in following order:
potatoes, onion, beef, onion, potatoes.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over entire casserole; cover and cook in microwave for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut crusts from bread.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Cut each slice of bread into quarters.
Arrange in layers in prepared baking dish, sprinkling each layer with raisins.
Beat eggs, just enough to blend thoroughly.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup sugar, milk and vanilla. Continue stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over bread and raisins.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix the sugar, peanuts and syrup in large glass container. Microwave 4 minutes on High; stir.
Microwave another 2 minutes on High.
Add margarine to mixture; microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High (1 1/2 minutes will give you a chewier candy; 2 minutes will turn out a crunchy candy).
Add the remaining ingredients (baking soda, vanilla and salt) quickly to the boiled mixture.
Stir until mixture is "foamy."
Pour onto buttered baking sheet; spread to desired thickness.
After cooling, break into pieces.
So easy.

title: baked scallops
directions: Butter a large casserole.
Beat eggs; salt and pepper. Roll scallops in egg mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn dodgers
directions: Mix all together and fry in hot grease.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl together at one time.
Pour into dish; chill for 3 hours.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with hand mixer until smooth.
(For thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons additional milk.) Grease heated griddle with shortening.
(Pastry brush can be used for this.)
To check if griddle or pan is hot enough, sprinkle few drops of water.
If it bubbles and skittles around, it's ready. Use 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Cook until golden on both sides.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: vegetables in foil
directions: On large square of foil, layer potatoes, beans, onions, celery and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil, garlic powder, thyme and parsley flakes.
Sprinkle with oil and cover tightly. Grill on low fire about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: cherry pecan ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, half and half and vanilla in a large bowl. Then add Jell-O, cherries and pecans; then pour in a freezer container.
Finish filling with milk.
Freeze according to instructions.

title: cherry dessert(serves 12)
directions: Place cherry pie filling in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts over filling.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes.

title: he-man spanish rice
directions: In skillet cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until vegetables are tender.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover, bring to a boil and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fluffy frosting(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine sugar, water, sugar replacement, egg whites and cream of tartar in top of a double boiler; beat at high speed for 1 minute.
Set over simmering water in the bottom of the double boiler.
Continue to beat at high speed for 4 to 5 minutes, or until soft peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla to frosting; continue beating at high speed 1 to 2 minutes, or until thick enough to spread on a cooled cake.

title: corn cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop onto hot skillet with a large spoon.
(These are small pancakes.)
Cook on both sides until golden brown.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Delicious!
Make sure to cook some bacon up on the side!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together Nestle
Quik and red food coloring and set aside. Cream together
butter,
sugar,
eggs, milk (butter or sour), flour and
vanilla.
Add coloring mixture slowly.
Beat 10 minutes with electric mixer.
Then mix together vinegar and soda;
add to batter
slowly
by
hand.
Bake
at
350° for 35 minutes.

title: micky's jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
When Jell-O begins to set, add pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Combine Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Spread over Jell-O.
Combine sugar, eggs, lemon juice, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook until slightly thickened, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Pour over top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: stir in the pan chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients
together and put into ungreased 8 1/2 x 11 1/2 baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Bake at 350° until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick a few times with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until soft.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out the pulp.
Put in a bowl.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to potato pulp.
Stir and blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into potato mixture.
Fill potato shells with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine sugar and Mazola.
Add egg and beat well. Add nut meats and vanilla. Fold in mixed and sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares while warm.
Makes 16.

title: squash bisque
directions: Cook to tender.
Put through Foley food mill or blender.
Serve hot or cold with a dab of yogurt.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Let cool. Add the cranberries, nuts, pineapple and lemon juice.
Pour into shallow pan. Chill until firm.
You can add 3/4 cup chopped celery, if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large container, put cukes and onions; add 1/2 cup salt. Cover with ice cubes and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Drain off liquid; set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients in a large pan. Heat and add onions and cukes.
Bring to a boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; stir until thick.
Add strawberries; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line pan with wax paper; cover with a layer of strawberry mixture.
Add a layer of vanilla wafers.
Continue until all mixture is used.
Finish with a layer of vanilla wafers.
Chill thoroughly.
Turn out on cake plate.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients to dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients at once using a spoon.
Bake 1 hour 10 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together sugar, flour and orange rind.
Add fruit and mix well.
Put into pie crust.
Dot with margarine.
Cut strips from top crust and make a lattice top. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: On a platter, layer beans and taco seasoning.
Next layer sour cream and salsa.
Add lettuce, tomato, black olives and cheese. Chill 1 hour.
Pour chips in bowl and serve.

title: uncooked peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except powdered sugar.
Slowly add powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Pack in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken-zucchini casserole
directions: Saute carrots, zucchini and onion in skillet sprayed with Pam. Add chicken.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups stuffing, seasoning, 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can water (can add more water if you want it less dry).
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with rest of stuffing.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: peanut cream candy
directions: Mix sugars, salt and cream.
Boil gently without stirring, to soft ball stage (236°).
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Add peanut butter and flavorings.
Mix until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Cool.

title: spinach salad with crisp red chiles(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Discard spinach stems and yellow or wilted leaves.
Wash thoroughly and pat dry.
Wrap in paper towels and enclose in plastic bag.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Do the same with watercress.
Cut chiles crosswise into thin strips; discard seeds and stems.
In a 10 or 12-inch frying pan, stir in oil and chiles over low heat until chiles are crisp, about 2 to 3 minutes. Lift chiles from oil and set aside.
Save oil for dressing.
If cactus pad has needles, hold with tongs and scrape clean with knife.
Peel pad if skin is tough.
Cut cactus into 1/2-inch squares.
In a 3 or 4-quart pan, bring about 8 cups of water to a boil; add cactus and reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 5 minutes or until cactus is barely tender when pierced with fork.
Tear spinach into bite sized pieces and place half of the spinach in a large salad bowl.
Top with half of the watercress, onion, cactus, radishes and cheese.
Repeat layers to serve.
Peel and pit the avocados; slice and arrange on top of the salad with the chiles.

title: pistachio pie(delicious, easy to prepare dessert)
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll out half of pastry and line a 9-inch pie plate.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Refrigerate pastry until ready to use.

title: eggplant bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix crumbs, oregano and garlic salt.
Dip eggplant slices in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in single layer in greased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch. Spread evenly with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and 2 cups of water. Add beans.
Return to fire and cook 5 minutes.
Add chips; mix well.
Spread mixture into baking dish.
Add cheese on top.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: pecan bars
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour and add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake.
Refrigerate.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Microwave chili and cream cheese for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove and mix thoroughly.
Return to microwave for another 2 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Microwave about 30 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Serve with Tostitos chips. Easy and tasty.

title: cocktail quiche
directions: Drain, seed and chop peppers.
Mix peppers and cheeses.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Add salt to eggs and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: mediterranean shrimp with linguine
directions: Prepare linguine and keep warm.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add shrimp and cook 4 minutes, stirring frequently until shrimp is just pink.
Using slotted spoon, transfer shrimp to plate.

title: appetizer-quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, additional 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and green and red pepper.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: crusted sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done.
Peel and mash (should be about 3 cups of cooked, mashed sweet potatoes).
Combine with sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Turn into greased casserole.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Marinate 8 to 10 pork chops in sauce overnight.
Place pork chops in shallow roasting pan and pour sauce over them.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve over hot buttered rice.

title: greek oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes. Cut each lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Place wedges in a bowl with cold water. Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain. Pat dry with paper towels.
Toss potatoes with oil.
Place skin side down on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Combine oregano, pepper and salt.
Sprinkle evenly over potatoes. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and browned. Remove from oven and sprinkle with vinegar.
Serve oven fries immediately.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains about 117 calories per 4 wedges.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Let set in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out and glaze while hot.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars in microwave oven.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until served.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients and cook on hot griddle.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and oleo.
Mix Stove Top dressing according to directions.
Add cream of chicken soup and chopped carrots to the saute mix.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Put 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of baking dish.
Add all other ingredients.
Top with the rest of the Stove Top dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of fresh vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, onion, one of the vegetable and seasoning combos following.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for the time indicated or until vegetables are tender (remove bay leaf if using broccoli).
Place 1/2 of vegetables in blender, cover and blend 30 to 60 seconds, until smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Repeat with remaining mixture and set all aside.

title: heavenly pears
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine and mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into large deep baking dish.
Place sliced peaches on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine the crushed crackers, melted butter and sugar. Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Scald milk and butter in saucepan. Beat egg slightly; add sugar and vanilla. Stir into scalded milk. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° until pie barely shakes in crust. Shake nutmeg over pie before baking.

title: jigglers
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water or juice.
Pour into molds. Chill about 3 hours.
Dip pan in warm water.
Cut into shapes.

title: perfect creamy cauliflower soup
directions: In heavy soup kettle, melt butter.
Add oil.
Add onion, scallions and garlic.
Add celery and cauliflower.
Add seasonings.
Mix well and cook, uncovered, over medium heat for several minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water and miso.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
Remove cover and cool slightly. Puree in small increments in blender until smooth and creamy. Reheat, adding fresh ground nutmeg, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: the best horseradish sauce
directions: Mix together well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until serving time.

title: 3-cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill until firm enough to shape into ball.
Roll in nuts and wrap with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: brown rice and chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot, except almonds.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or automatic 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with almonds on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cooked chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add canned cream and margarine. Cook until thick, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: holiday wreaths
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Add Kellogg's corn flakes cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Portion warm cereal mixture using 1/4 cup dry measure. Using buttered fingers, quickly shape into individual wreaths. Dot with red cinnamon candies.
Yields 16 wreaths.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients. Close the bag and shake to cover potatoes with soup mix and oil. Empty potatoes into a shallow baking pan. Bake for 40 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli slightly in salted water.
Drain.
Debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Put broccoli in buttered casserole.
Put chicken over broccoli.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain and combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix together and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Better if made the day before.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Caution:
Skillet must be greased and hot before adding cornmeal mixture.
Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Grate cheese; set aside.
Combine onions, hot peppers; set aside.
Place a 9-inch iron skillet, greased well, in a hot oven.
Mix all dry ingredients, add eggs, oil, milk and corn.
Remove hot skillet from oven.
Put 1/2 of corn meal mixture in skillet.
Spread cheese over mixture.
Then sprinkle hamburger over cheese.
Sprinkle onions and pepper over hamburger.
Cover with rest of corn meal mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, water and butter in a saucepan.
Boil to soft boil stage (236°).
Cool, then beat in the evaporated milk, a little salt and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and serve on ice cream, pudding or cake.
Makes 2 cups.

title: oat whole wheat pancakes
directions: Stir dry ingredients to mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except egg whites, and stir.
Fold in egg whites, beaten.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix ingredients together to make sauce.
Brown 1 1/2 pounds ground beef; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain meat.
Mix the sauce with the meat and simmer.
Serve on bun or by itself.

title: baby cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl and beat with electric mixer until smooth. Line muffin tins with paper liners and put one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each liner.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixer.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.
Cover with pie filling.
Chill.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cheese together.
Mix in pineapple and juice.
Put in baking dish.
Top with melted butter and crushed crackers.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons and oranges.
Add sugar and enough water to make a gallon.

title: russian tea
directions: Add above ingredients to tea mixture.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 Gallon (16 cups).

title: barbecue ribs ala hartford
directions: Mix together the seasonings and brown sugar.
Roll ribs in this mixture.
Pat any remaining mixture onto the ribs.
Place ribs in a roasting pan.
Mix together the vinegar and tomato soup and pour over the ribs.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn ribs and continue baking, uncovered, for another hour.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix together
and
form into small balls. Roll balls in coconut, pecans or powdered sugar.

title: quick lemon cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Cream shortening; add sugar and pudding mix.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture; beat thoroughly until well blended.

title: green bean-mushroom medley
directions: Heat 1-inch water in 2-quart pan to boiling.
Add beans and carrots.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until tender, about 12 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and stir onion and mushrooms in margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in beans, carrots, salt, m.s.g., garlic salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat, 5 minutes.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and shortening.
Mix yeast, water and buttermilk.
Pour out on floured board and roll out 1/2-inch.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400°.

title: baja lasagne
directions: Saute onion in nonstick skillet.
Add tomatoes, chilies, mushrooms, beans, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put half tortilla strips down.
Pour 1/4 tomato mixture and 1/3 cheese over tortillas.
Repeat layers, ending with sour cream and last 1/4 of tomato mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Put candy bars in freezer.
Bake cake in sheet pan; cool. Make pudding 5 minutes before you start to layer (don't let it firm itself or it will be too hard to spread).
Remove candy bars and shatter into little pieces.
Now you are ready to layer.
Use a punch bowl for serving dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, about 5 minutes. Mix together the soup, mayonnaise, chopped onion, cubed Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Pour broccoli and combined ingredients in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven about 50 to 60 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: tuna cheese log
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat together the cheeses.
Stir in the celery, onion, mayonnaise, hot pepper sauce and tuna.
Shape the mixture into 5-inch roll, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Before serving, roll in chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; add other ingredients.
Cook all ingredients until thick.

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place brisket into oven bag.
Add chili sauce and water.
Mix well.
Poke holes in top of cooking bag. Place in baking pan.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix and make in cakes.
Place on wax paper and chill 15 minutes.
Fry in oil.
Makes 8 crab cakes.

title: barry's pecan pralines
directions: Put 3/4 cup of dry sugar in a medium saucepan. Heat on medium-high until sugar melts and turns a rich brown (beer bottle brown). After sugar has melted and turned brown, add evaporated milk, being careful not to let it boil over. Once it settles down, add remaining ingredients and heat to "soft-ball" stage, about 20 minutes on medium-high heat (electric stove) and close to high heat on a gas stove.

title: mom's old-fashioned burnt sugar cake
directions: Place 1 cup sugar in skillet and heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and becomes brown.
Remove from heat.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to mixture with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Recipe makes 1 loaf; can be doubled or tripled if more is desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: fruity parfait
directions: You put into a tall glass each ingredient in a layer (in order given).

title: quick and easy corn casserole
directions: Combine milk, cheese, corn and nutmeg in a medium bowl and mix well.
Spoon evenly into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing mix evenly on top.
