Pour melted butter evenly on top. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place breasts in casserole.
Cover with soups and let bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Add water to make 3 cups liquid. Add puddings and orange juice concentrate to liquid.
Cook until thick; stir constantly.
Cool to room temperature and then stir in fruit and sliced bananas.
Chill.

title: joe froggers
directions: Mix sugar and the shortening.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sugar.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 3-inch circles; sprinkle with sugar.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake until almost no imprint remains when touched in the center, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool about 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: tabouli
directions: Boil stock, add salt and bulgar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover pot and let sit for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain excess water.
Chill.
Toss with all other ingredients.
Adjust to taste.

title: carrot cake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Add flour, then carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 24 hour pea salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onions, celery, peppers and peas.
In a small bowl, mix Miracle Whip and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on top of salad, making sure you spread to the edges.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top and cover with aluminum foil.
Let sit in fridge for 24 hours.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse the beans.
In a large Dutch oven cover beans with with 6 cups cold water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 1 hour (or soak beans overnight in a covered pan).
Drain and rinse the beans.
In the same Dutch oven combine rinsed beans, 6 cups hot water, ham bone, onion, garlic, bay leaf and red pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix together. Dust with paprika. Bake at 300 degrees for 20 minutes or until lightly brown on top. Eat warm on crackers.

title: alarm chili
directions: Cook ground beef in 2 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until well done, stirring until crumbly.
Remove ground beef with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.
Drain and wipe saucepan.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper with 1/2 cup tomatoes in oil in saucepan for 3 minutes.
Add oregano, cumin, chili powder, cocoa, sugar, hot pepper and Tabasco sauce. Cook for 3 minutes.
Add beans, ground beef and remaining tomatoes.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce(pastor burns' famous recipe)
directions: Fry hamburger, pepperoni, onion, celery and mango; drain. Pour fried ingredients in a large saucepan.
Add spaghetti sauce. Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add mustard, sugar, salt, pepper, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper (optional); stir.
Simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Turn oven to 300°.
Put margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt in oven, then remove.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mix with margarine.
When oven is heated, pour pecans into margarine-Worcestershire mixture and stir to coat pecans.
Place in oven.
Stir pecans every 10 minutes.
Salt as needed.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned goulash
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in skillet, then add canned tomatoes and Ragu sauce.
Bring to low boil, then add cheese.
Simmer until cheese is completely melted.
Boil elbows until done, then mix together.

title: tune up a tuna
directions: In a bowl, stir soup, eggs, tuna and pimento.
Set aside.
Mix Bisquick mix and hot water.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth.
Press dough into bottom and up sides of greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on dough.
Add tuna mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and garnish with additional pimento.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set. Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice until almost soft. Cool, then mix with rest of ingredients, except soup. Stuff peppers with mixture. Place in casserole dish. Pour tomato soup over peppers. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage dip - mexican style
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Mix softened cream cheese with drained Ro-Tel.
Add sausage last.
Serve in a crock-pot with tostada style chips.
Everybody loves this one!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour and soda.
Mash bananas and whip until very light.
Add bananas and nuts.
Turn in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fried ripples(love knots)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll as thin as pie crust.
Cut into strips and splash and fry in deep hot fat until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: unfried chicken and fries
directions: Place oven racks in middle and lower position.
Heat to 425°. Coat a large wire rack and a large baking sheet with nonstick spray, set rack in a roasting pan.
To make breading, mix first set of dry ingredients in large zip lock bag.
Mix yogurt, 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper in a small bowl.
Rub on chicken 1 piece at a time, place in bag, seal and shake to coat.
Arrange on wire rack; coat chicken with nonstick spray.
Cut each potato in 8 wedges. Season with remaining salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in a single layer on baking sheet; coat potato with non-stick spray.
Bake chicken on middle rack, potatoes on lower rack, 30 - 35 minutes turning potatoes once, until chicken and potatoes are cooked through and browned.
Serves 4-6.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Make your favorite biscuit dough.
Roll out thin on floured board.
Cover dough with butter and sugar, then roll dough up. Cut in slices about 1/2-inch thick, then put in skillet.
Cook in 425° oven until well browned.
Pour 1 cup sweet milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla, mixed, over rolls and bake again for a few minutes until bubbly hot.
Can add nutmeg or spice of your choice.

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: You will also need wooden toothpicks.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Blend milk and pudding.
When it begins to thicken, blend in cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Plug hole in pot with waxed paper.
Line inside of pot with Reynolds Wrap.
Layer mixture with cookies.
Top with cookies.
Decorate with a flower.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease 3 loaf pans and fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Preboil potatoes 15 minutes. Peel and cut into half, lengthway pieces. Place in buttered baking dish. Combine sugar, salt, butter and water in a saucepan. Boil 3 minutes. Pour syrup over potatoes. Bake at moderate temperature, 350°, for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Baste occasionally. Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Let spinach thaw enough that it can be broken up well.
Mix all ingredients and let sit about 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables such as cauliflower, carrots, celery, squash, etc.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Sprinkle cheese over cut side. Separate onion slices into rings and place over cheese. Sprinkle thick layer of bread crumbs over onion.
Bake, cut side up on shallow baking pan, in moderate oven about 50 minutes.
Cut into desired serving size. Good way to use oversized zucchini.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, 6 minutes, or until mixture boils, stirring occasionally, during last half of cooking time.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix Ranch style dressing mix, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower, then let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, add bacon.
Ready to eat!!

title: fantastic brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter (if using melted chocolate mix with butter in pan) over low heat.
Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add chocolate and melted butter and mix altogether.
Put it in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan and spread.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chili con queso(nacho cheese dip)
directions: Heat oil in a saucepan.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender, but not browned.
Add chilies and tomatoes.
Lower heat and add cheese.
Cook until melted.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook until heated, but don't boil.
Serving in a crock-pot works well.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Saute onion in oil; stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, salt, garlic, oregano and beans.
Beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients, reserving 2 cups cheese for topping.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, layer noodles, tomato mixture and spinach-cheese mixture.
Use 1/3 tomato sauce for first layer, 1/2 noodles and 1/2 spinach mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top layer should be tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
May be frozen to use later.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: On salad plate, arrange spinach leaves, chicken, fruit, celery, almonds and green onions.
In a dish, mix together the mayonnaise and orange juice; drizzle over chicken mixture. Garnish with orange slices and strawberries.
Serves 2.

title: dallas' chocolate chip
directions: Cream butter, vegetable shortening, sugar and brown sugar for 5 minutes.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Put teaspoon size clumps on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of a baking dish; add beef consomme soup plus 1/2 soup can water.
Place pork chops on top; salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: slaw
directions: In saucepan, mix together eggs, sugar, cream and vinegar. Bring to boil until thickened.
Pour over cabbage and it's ready to serve.

title: polly's cabbage rolls
directions: Cut core out of the cabbage. Place in a large pot with enough water to cover cabbage. Bring to a boil and continue to boil until cabbage leaves are soft. As it boils, carefully remove
so it doesn't take too long and the leaves don't get mushy. Drain cabbage in a colander.

title: no bake honey crispers
directions: Place a sheet of waxed paper on a baking pan that will fit inside your refrigerator.
Measure coconut and place in pie pan; set aside.
Measure powdered sugar, peanut butter and honey and place in medium bowl.
Use a rubber spatula to get peanut butter and honey out of the measuring cups.
Stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Add cereal and raisins.
Stir well.
By hand, roll pieces of mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in coconut and place on waxed paper in baking pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Check to test firmness.
If not firm, wait for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: tuna and pasta cheddar melt
directions: Cook pasta in broth and water in skillet until tender; do not drain. Add soup, milk and tuna. Top with cheese. Mix bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle on top. Heat through.

title: sweet and crunchy party mix
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and repeat.
Add vanilla and soda and stir. Combine cereal, pretzels and nuts in brown paper bag.
Pour syrup mixture over all and shake sack to coat.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again and repeat.
Spread out to cool.
Add bag of M&M's when cooled.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add Coke.
Let jello set until soft set.
Stir in cream cheese (broken into small pieces) and nuts.
Finish letting jell.
Makes 4 servings.

title: aloha pies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Stir well to coat fruit, pepper and wieners with sauce. Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Stir halfway through cooking.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Cook on low heat until thickens.
Remove from heat.
Slice bananas and layer them with wafers and pudding.

title: fast pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Whip last 2 ingredients with a fork. Add ingredients together and put in a pan.
If you want thick dough, use 9-inch.
For thinner dough, use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press dough in bottom of pan.
Add 1 large can of fruit filling for 9-inch pan or 2 large cans for 9 x 13-inch.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: In skillet, saute the onion and bell pepper until soft. Add the other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour
or
until
all ingredients are done.
Cook 1 package of
spaghetti in boiling salted
water until tender.
Drain in a
colander.	Serve
the meat sauce over the spaghetti.

title: frozen peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Pour
half
and
half into large bowl.	Add pie filling mix. Beat
with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and chopped candies. Spoon
into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving. Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in butter; remove from heat.
Place chicken soup, water and spices in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Put rice in casserole dish; pour all except 1/3 of soup mixture over rice. Place chicken on top and then pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: new york style cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Fold in sour cream.

title: pork chop-rice casserole
directions: Salt and fry pork chops.
Set aside.
Place unwashed rice in baking dish.
Add consomme, bell pepper, onion, water and celery. Stir to mix.
Lay pork chops on top and cover dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until rice is flaky and tender.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in greased large casserole dish.
Cover with diluted soup and thin layer of cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no-crust coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey pie
directions: Cook chicken 3 to 3 1/2 hours. When done, set aside to cool. Take meat from bones and cut up in cubes.
Make a medium white sauce.
Melt margarine in skillet over low heat. Blend in flour, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in broth and heavy cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cook peas and carrots as directions on package.
Put chicken and vegetables in white sauce and mix well. Turn into pastry lined pie pan and bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes or until brown.

title: homemade cheese soup
directions: Boil
cabbage,	carrots,
celery, onion, soup and water until vegetables	are
tender.
Set aside.
In a skillet make white sauce with butter, flour and milk; add to other mixture, cook until
smooth.
Add
cheese,
pepper and tomatoes.	Cook until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and mix in sugar and syrup.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until well done.

title: cheese surprise appetizer
directions: Mix cheese, butter and flour to form dough.
Shape into small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Flatten ball with hands; place one olive in center, wrap dough around it, sealing edges completely.
Freeze until just before ready to serve.
(These must be frozen.)

title: eye of round roast
directions: Put meat in a large size brown n' bag. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour meat. Bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: mexican fish sticks
directions: Arrange fish sticks in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: toffee
directions: Butter square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Spread pecans in pan. Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, for
7 minutes.
Immediately spread mixture evenly over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over candy; cover pan to contain heat.
Spread melted chocolate over candy while hot; cut or break into small pieces.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in a medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times; roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place biscuits on an ungreased sheet.
Let rise in a warm place about 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown. Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: zucchini bites
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon mixture into well-greased mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: ladies home journal "award winning" homestyle baked beans
directions: Empty baked beans in a large bowl. Fry bacon to a crisp.
Keep the oil.
Saute onion and green pepper. Empty in bowl.
Peel or squeeze the orange juice into bowl. Chop or grind the orange peelings.
Place in the bowl. Stir in the oil from bacon in the bowl also.
Stir in the Brer Rabbit molasses. Combine all the ingredients into bowl.
Stir well.
Place baked beans and all ingredients into a baking dish. Bake 45 minutes until thickens at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Heat margarine and milk; pour over sugar and salt and stir well.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat egg slightly and add to milk mixture.
Combine the two mixtures and stir in flour.
With lightly greased hands, mold dough into a ball.
Place in bowl rubbed with oil and store in refrigerator.
About 3 1/2 hours before baking, knead and make into rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Bake or boil eggplants and cool them.
When cold, scoop out the centers and the chopped onion, the oil and vinegar.
Salt and pepper.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak All-Bran in milk, molasses and egg, which has been mixed together until soft.
Add oil.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to liquid ingredients, gently stirring just until flour disappears.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine and microwave on High for 4 minutes the sugar and syrup.
Stir and add peanuts.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Add butter and vanilla.
Stir and microwave for 1 minute. Stir in baking powder.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until done; don't salt.
Pull off bones and put aside, saving broth.
Stir together dressing mixes, onion and melted butter.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch dish, put a layer of dressing crumbs, a layer of chicken and a layer of mushroom soup diluted with a can of broth.
Repeat with another layer of crumbs, chicken and cream of chicken soup, diluted with a can of broth. Top with a layer of crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: All cheeses should be at room temperature.
Cream ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chipped beef.

title: calico bean pot
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of fat in skillet.
Add onion and beef to skillet.
Saute until onion is tender and beef is brown.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: pistachio salad #2
directions: Mix well,
then
add 16 ounce carton Cool Whip and mix. Chill 1 hour.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, cottage cheese and Jell-O (straight from the box).
Blend thoroughly.
Add the fruits and chill.

title: becky's banana nut bread
directions: Soften butter and mix all ingredients.
Bake 50 - 60 minutes at 350.

title: fish souffle
directions: Melt butter, add flour and, when smooth, stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add seasoning and crumbs.
Cool.
Add flaked fish to sauce and mix well.
Stir in egg yolks and stiffly beaten whites.
Put in greased baking dish and bake in moderately hot oven until firm.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Bake brownies; pour coffee flavor over them as they cool. Make the pudding and let it set in refrigerator awhile.
When brownies are cooled and pudding set, layer as follows:
layer brownies (crumbled), layer pudding, layer Whipped Creme, top with crushed candy.
Start next layer; depending on size of the dish you use, you can get 2 to 3 layers.

title: "dirt" cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk.
Blend pudding and cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Prepare dirt by crumbling Oreos with rolling pin or food processor.
Layer in cups or flowerpot, 3 layers of Oreos and 2 of pudding mixture.
Put gummy worms on top.
Foil wrapped plant can be added if desired.
Makes enough for two 5 1/2-inch pots.

title: bean soup
directions: Place beans in kettle; cover in water. Add 2 teaspoons salt; soak overnight or boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let sit for 1 hour. Drain. Add 2 quarts of water and ham hock. Simmer 2 hours. Add veggies and seasonings. Simmer 1 hour or place in crock-pot. Add juice of 1 lemon. Top with cheese and sour cream.

title: cheese strudel
directions: Unroll one can of Pillsbury crescent roll dough on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Spread filling on crescent roll dough.
Unroll remaining crescent roll dough and place on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Dredge pork in flour.
Brown in oil until done.
Remove from pan.
For sauce, saute onion in drippings.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water, vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple liquid. Cook over low heat.
Stir until thick.
Serve on skewers.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits well.
Combine with marshmallows and nuts; let set.
Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar, cream and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook in double boiler until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over fruit mixture and mix lightly.
Chill in fruit molds or bowls for 24 hours.

title: near-cast white bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and bring to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Saute onion and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add to beans with other ingredients.
Cook, covered, until beans are tender.
Mash beans slightly and serve.
Makes about 1 1/2-quarts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients and add Cool Whip.

title: three cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except margarine and Parmesan cheese until stiff dough forms.
Turn dough onto surface well dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll in mix to coat.
Shape into ball.
Knead 10 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chicken salad(easy - 20 minutes)
directions: Rinse lettuce; drain well.
Tear into small pieces.
Clean and slice mushrooms.
Rinse tomatoes and cucumber.
Cut chicken into small chunks.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Peel and slice cucumber. Chop nuts coarsely.
Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Garnish with watercress or parsley.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients well. Chill in refrigerator until served.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: tater tot slop
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In same skillet saute onions; add up to 1 cup water (not to runny); heat through.
Cook Tater Tots then line the bottom of a casserole dish, add meat mixture; top with cheese.
Bake 350 until cheese melts.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
This is a different dip from the regular dips.
Serve with fruit.

title: john's favorite pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; mix.
Add remaining ingredients; mix with fork until large lumps disappear.
Grease griddle.
Heat on medium-high until a few drops of water sizzle. Pour batter onto hot griddle.
Turn pancakes over when bubbles form and edges start to dry.
Cook on other side until desired brownness.
Serves 6.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and chill.
Forms 2 balls.
Roll in walnuts and serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Drain cabbage and place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with pepper. Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Sprinkle cheese on top and pour evaporated milk over ingredients.
Bake at 400° until bubbly on top, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate angel food cake(low sugar)
directions: Combine flour packet from cake mix with the unsweetened cocoa. Prepare the cake according to package directions.
Fold the chocolate flavoring into batter.
Bake in a tube pan (according to package directions).
When cooled, remove from pan.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on the package, using the juice from the drained pineapple for a portion of the liquid.
Set until this jells.
Soften the cream cheese and beat the jello into the cheese.
Fold in the whipped cream, mayonnaise, drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a jello mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: recovery soup
directions: Saute beef in large 8-quart pot. Add onion and garlic. Drain off fat. Add all ingredients in order listed. Bring to a boil. Reduce to low heat and let simmer about 1/2 hour. Stir frequently. Good served with corn muffins.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Add all ingredients in 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
As cheese melts, you may need to stir to mix well.

title: elephant ears
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Let set 20 minutes.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Stack with wax paper between each piece. Heat vegetable oil in large, heavy skillet.
Drop in hot grease after it has been stretched out in large circle.
Turn once. Should be lightly browned.
Surface will bubble or blister.
Turn with spatula and broad knife.
Place on paper towel.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture or top with canned fruit pie.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery in chicken broth until done.
Mix bread crumbs; add onions, celery, sage, parsley flakes and eggs.
Mix well.
Add diluted soup and enough chicken broth to make the mixture slightly thin.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese. Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla and flour. Add salt. Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven and bake at 300° for 2 hours. Let cool for 15 minutes on wire rack.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix together and bake covered 30 minutes at 325°.
Then bake 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken delight
directions: Blend soups together and set aside.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Stir rice into melted butter in casserole dish.
Blend in 1/2 of soup mixture into rice.
Mix chicken pieces into remaining soup mixture and spread on top of rice mixture. Top with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not drain corn.
Pour into 9x13 glass or metal baking pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Pour in a flat dish.
Cool, but not jelled firm.
Make crust with graham crackers and butter. Blend sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together.
(Whip milk separate.)
Drain pineapple dry; add all ingredients to milk, also Jell-O.
Pour over crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: guilt-free sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed until combined. Gradually add egg substitute, beating well.
Combine sour cream and baking soda; stir well and set aside.
Combine flour and salt; with mixer running at low speed, add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan. Cool on wire rack.

title: favorite homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with sugar.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine yeast mixture, salt and oil. Stir in cracked wheat and flours.
Mix well.
On a floured board, knead dough for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let rise in a large oiled pan or bowl for approximately 2 hours.
Punch down, turn over and let rise again for 1 hour.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Knead each part vigorously and shape into loaves.
Place loaves into 4 greased bread loaf pans.
Allow to rise for 30 minutes.

title: yams on the half shell
directions: Bake yams at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Slice off top 1/3 and scoop out.
Add all other ingredients except 1/2 marmalade.
Whip with beater; replace in shells.
Bake 15 minutes and drizzle with remaining marmalade during last 5 minutes.
(Can be done ahead and frozen, but better to refrigerate, set out at room temperature a while before baking last 15 minutes.)

title: grilled asparagus
directions: Wash and trim fresh asparagus; roll in olive oil.
Sprinkle with basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Broil 7 minutes.

title: lemon tart
directions: Whisk eggs, sugar, cornmeal and flour together.
Mix melted margarine, milk, lemon juice and rind; then add together.
Pour into pie crust and bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: icebox relish
directions: Cut cabbages, onions, tomatoes and green and red bell peppers finely.
Add salt and mix.
Let set for 30 minutes or longer. Squeeze dry with hands or in a bag.
Add remaining ingredients. Keep in refrigerator.
Keeps several weeks.

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash with fork. Combine with remaining ingredients; blend well.
Refill the whites, using approximately 2 teaspoons mixture per egg half. Makes 16 deviled eggs.

title: scrumptious chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press half of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; spread with chocolate mixture. Sprinkle rest of crumbs over filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: angel kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to beat.
Fold in pecans and dates.
Drop in teaspoons on foil-covered cookie sheets.
Place in preheated 375° oven, turn oven off and leave overnight.
Do not open oven.
This requires 3 cookie sheets.
Arrange oven racks to accommodate before heating.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Saut onions in butter until light brown.
Drain well.
Combine chicken, celery, mayonnaise, garlic, salt, black pepper and drained almonds.
Toss lightly to coat ingredients evenly with mayonnaise. Serve chilled.

title: sliced pineapple sparkle
directions: In small pan, combine water, cinnamon and cloves; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Strain.
Cool.
Add sweetener and fruit juices.
Chill.
Serve over ice cubes with cinnamon sticks muddlers.
Makes 12 cups.

title: party chicken
directions: Shred
beef
slightly
and cover bottom of flat greased baking dish.
Wrap
chicken breasts with bacon and arrange on beef.
Mix soup
and sour cream together;
pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered,	at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add broccoli that has been cooked and drained.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add mustard, sugar, salt and parsley.
Stir.
Add carrots and stir until glazed, about 5 minutes.

title: grape meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and shape into small balls. Cook until brown.
Mix together jelly and chili sauce.
Cook over moderate heat until heated through.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer 60 minutes.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Brown beef with green pepper and onion; drain well. Add green olives and seasonings.
Place in shallow ovenproof casserole. Spoon sour cream over meat mixture, then pour beans evenly over sour cream layer. Sprinkle with corn chips, then cheese.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through and cheese melts.
Serve plain or over shredded lettuce or hot rice. Serves 6.

title: blueberry crunch dessert
directions: Pour undrained pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread blueberries over pineapple. Sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar over this mixture. Sprinkle the box of dry cake mix on top of the sugar. Next, drizzle the melted margarine over the cake mix. Then sprinkle the pecans over this. Finally sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar over this. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Then stick with fork all over and bake for another 15 minutes longer.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, the margarine, shortening and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.

title: francis stevens' sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; drain and beat a little.
Add sugar and butter and continue to beat.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Pour in casserole dish and bake at 400° until done, about 1 hour.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put in enamel container.
Add 1 cup of salt and cover with boiling water.
When vinegar and water come to a boiling point, pack in jars.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt to each quart jar.
Cover with hot mixture and seal.

title: cheese tuna muffins
directions: Boil rice; drain.
Add cheese and tuna.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in cupcake pan for muffins.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Over the top:

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch pie pans.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour contents into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Pies make their own crust.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into greased deep dish pie pan.
Top with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt, bouillon cube, vinegar, catsup and soy sauce. Bring to a boil over medium heat on stove top. Stir mixture to dissolve sugar and bouillon cube. Remove from heat. Place wings in a crock-pot and cover with sauce. Cover and simmer 5 to 6 hours. Remove wings and increase heat to highest setting.

title: breadsticks with rosemary and sea salt
directions: Brush breadsticks with olive oil.
Sprinkle with rosemary and salt.
Bake in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.
Remove from oven. Brush with additional olive oil.
Add more rosemary and salt, if desired, to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: easy one-dish ham or chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soup, 1 cup milk, ham or chicken and onion powder in ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 450° for 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crabbies
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Quarter the muffins and freeze on cookie sheets.
Keep frozen until ready to use.
(May be stored in plastic bags.)

title: male chauvinist chili
directions: In large skillet, brown bacon pieces until crisp.
Remove from skillet; drain well.
Brown sausage and ground chuck with onions over medium heat.
Drain and place in crock-pot.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 12 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp and combine with other ingredients, mixing well. Chill before serving.
Delicious with crackers or corn chips.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Pour in spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes or longer.
Boil noodles, drain and rinse.
Mix beaten eggs with cottage cheese.
In oblong casserole dish, pour sauce (just enough to cover dish), layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and top with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Layers can be added by increasing recipe.

title: raisin cake
directions: *Or 3 teaspoons allspice.

title: carrots with bechamel sauce(venezuelan dish)
directions: Cut the carrots in thin slices.
In a deep pan, pour the water, salt and carrots (the water must cover the carrots).
Boil them for 15 minutes or until cooked, but firm.
Drain them.

title: summer salad with creamy lime-honey dressing(used as dessert or salad)
directions: In bowl, stir lime juice, water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add banana; set aside.
In large serving bowl, layer blueberries (reserve 1/2 cup for garnish), nectarines, strawberries, bananas, watermelon and grapes.
Garnish with 1/2 cup blueberries, kiwi and cherries.
Pour lime-sugar syrup over fruits.
Cover loosely and chill.
To serve, spoon an assortment of fruits and berries with some of the syrup into dessert bowls; top with Creamy Lime-Honey Dressing (recipe follows).

title: herring salad
directions: Mix together; add a little of the juice and a little mayo* for moisture.
Eat as side dish with rye bread or snack.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: On lightly floured surface, allow dough to stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, Parmesan cheese and your seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Roll out dough to 15 x 11-inch and press onto bottom and sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer cheese, meat sauce and your choice of pizza toppings, alternately. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: old fashion apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugars.
Mix flour, spices, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add flour mixture to oil mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Gets better with age, 1 or 2 days.

title: new england skillet dinner
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender in a large skillet.
Add carrots, cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Fill paper muffin cups (set in muffin tins).
Cream the cheese with sugar; beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful of mix into each cupcake.
Bake according to package directions.
Yields 30 cupcakes.

title: spinach salad ala rosemary
directions: Wash, dry and tear spinach into bite sized pieces.
Add thinly sliced red onion.
Peel and section the oranges.
Add to the spinach.
Pour the Catalina dressing (not too much).
Toss and serve.

title: taco salad bowl
directions: In a medium skillet, brown beef and minced garlic.
Drain fat; add chopped green chilies and undrained whole tomatoes with meat in skillet.
Uncover; simmer 30 minutes.
Shred cheese and lettuce; chop scallions and tomatoes.
In a large bowl put lettuce in; arrange chips around outer edge.
Place meat on lettuce; sprinkle cheese around meat and add onion, tomato and olives.
Top off with sour cream.

title: tastes like real "cow butter"
directions: Beat with mixer until white.
Then taste the difference.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Note:
To keep apples from browning, place them in a large bowl of slightly salted water.
Drain, although this minimal liquid will not affect flavor or texture.
